title: italian casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese and potatoes.
Cook 2 more minutes. Put 1/2 meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put sliced potatoes on top, then another 1/2 meat mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°. Cover tightly with foil.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cook 10 minutes more.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Mix water, rice, soup mix and vegetables; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Brown sausage; drain and add to soup mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered lightly.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole or baking dish.
Cook noodles as package label directs.
Drain well. Meanwhile, drain tuna fish and separate with a fork into large flakes.
Blend condensed soup with onion and milk.
Heat until soup steams.
Do not let boil.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Add sugar and butter and press into pie pan about 12 inches in size.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Season chicken and boil about 45 minutes; remove chicken and debone.
Add vermicelli to chicken broth and boil until tender. Drain noodles; do not rinse them.
While noodles are boiling, saute in butter the onion and bell pepper.
Mix onion and bell pepper into noodles.
Add soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes; mix well. Add deboned chicken and Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and salt and beat.
Add whipping cream and Carnation.
Add 2 quarts milk. Bring to boil over slow fire.
Cool.
Add flavoring and enough milk to fill gallon freezer.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water and sugar; add tea and spices.
Let stand about 6 minutes.
Add fruit juices when you serve.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all other ingredients gently.
Bake in a Pyrex dish approximately 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Ritz crackers.
Garnish with parsley or paprika.

title: easy vichyssoise
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Add half and half; stir in potato flakes.
Pour mixture into blender or mixing bowl; add cream cheese and salt.
Beat or blend until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Chill.
Garnish each serving with diced cucumber and chopped tomato.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg yolk, extract and flour and mix well.
Dip small amounts onto cookie sheet; place far enough apart to allow for spreading.
Place pecan half in center of each cookie.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Add apples, salt, water, sugar and cornstarch together and cook until it is bubbly.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Put in quart jars and process in pressure canner on 5 pounds pressure for 8 minutes.
One quart makes a large pie.

title: potato-topped casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off excess fat.
Use 9-inch square baking dish.
Place vegetables over meat.
Spread soup on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Save juice.
Cook juice with eggs, sugar and flour until thick.
Cool.
Add pasta (cooked).
Let stand overnight.

title: nutty pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Mix together pumpkin and brown sugar.
Add spices and salt. Mix well.
Stir in softened ice cream and continue stirring until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust; sprinkle with nuts and freeze until firm.

title: smooth jello salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Prepare Jell-O as directed.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, pour it into the cream cheese/Cool Whip mixture and blend together.
Cool.

title: pork chop roll
directions: Brown pork chops in a little margarine in a frying pan.
Add the onion and celery. Cook until golden brown.
Mix in the bread cubes, salt, pepper and parsley.
Or use Stove Top stuffing as directed on package.

title: anise hyssop cookies
directions: Use your favorite sugar cookie recipe, as Pat did.
Then she ground the seed pods of her anise hyssop plant and added 3 tablespoons to the recipe.

title: soap animals
directions: Pour water to 1/8 mark in measuring cup.
Fill the rest with flaky soap (Ivory, Dreft, etc.).
It will be thick.
Mix until smooth.
Add food color to desired colors.
Stir until blended. Pour or scoop mixture into favorite plastic cutter shapes.
Put tray in warm dry place for 2 to 4 days until hard.
Place in tub, sink or pool.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix meat, potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Fry in greased skillet until brown.

title: braised stuffed pork chops
directions: For stuffing, trim some of the crust from bread and cut bread into 1/4-inch cubes.
In 1/4 cup of hot butter in a large skillet, saute chopped onion and celery, stirring until onion is golden, about 5 minutes.
Add bread cubes; stir to combine.
Remove from heat and add chopped parsley, raisins, salt, marjoram and pepper. Toss lightly to combine.
Wipe pork chops with damp paper towel. Trim excess fat; reserve fat and cut a pocket in each chop.
Fill each with 1/4 cup of stuffing.
Fasten with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix together the flour and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Coat both sides of chops with flour mixture and reserve remaining flour.
In a large saucepot, heat butter and reserved fat.
Over low heat, brown chops well on both sides, turning with tongs about 10 minutes on each side.
Remove and set aside.
Pour off fat.
To drippings, add remaining flour mixture.
Add apple juice, stirring constantly and boil 3 minutes.
Stand chops in bottom of saucepot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.

title: cheesy crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add sherry and mix with wire whisk.
Add flour and whisk constantly.
Slowly add milk, stirring until sauce starts to thicken.
Then add paprika, salt and pepper.
Taste for proper seasonings, then with wooden spoon stir in the cheeses until completely melted.
Drain noodles and toss with crab meat.
Place in greased 3-quart casserole, then pour warm sauce and mix well.
Bake 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: blond brownies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt, adding slowly and blending well. Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate bits; mix well.
Batter will be thick.
Spread evenly in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cocoa buttermilk sheet cake
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and add dry ingredients (sugar, flour and soda).
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Pour batter on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together well and put
in
jar.
Makes
quart dry mix. Use 2 teaspoons per cup for a good cup of hot tea.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil the crushed pineapple, sugar and water; add apricot jello.
Add cold water, softened cream cheese, pecans and carrots.
Cool until mixture begins to congeal.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix all together, adding cherry pie filling last.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 15-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° according to time on cake mix package.
Frost with fudge frosting.

title: yellow cake with caramel icing
directions: Mix margarine and add sugar, then eggs, then blend with flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix by hand and serve with crackers.

title: low calorie topping
directions: Blend until smooth.
Use as substitute for sour cream.
Makes 2 cups.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, butter and sugar to form crust. Press crust into pan.
Slice bananas and layer over crust.
Slice ice cream 1/2-inch thick and place over bananas.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place in freezer until firm.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased muffin pans.
Bake in 450° oven until done.

title: pepper cheese-stuffed burgers
directions: Divide ground beef into 8 equal portions.
Shape each into 4-inch diameter patties.
Place equal amount of cheese in center of 4 patties.
Press edges together to seal securely.
Place patties on grid over medium coals.
Grill 10 to 12 minutes or to desired doneness, turning once.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Toast buns on grill 1 minute, if desired.

title: elephant stew
directions: Take elephant.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over a slow fire for 4 weeks.
This will serve 3,468 people.
If more are expected, add 1 rabbit, but do this only if absolutely necessary; most people don't like to find a hare in their stew!

title: rice and beans
directions: Cook rice.
Set aside.
Saute onions and garlic powder in olive oil.
Fry ham and pepperoni with sauteed onions.
Add black-eyed peas.
Saute.
Add cooked rice.
Add parsley and pepper.
Mix it up and cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with pork.

title: shrimp commodore
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour, then water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Add seasonings. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Blend in tomato juice; add shrimp and heat thoroughly, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: seafood stroganoff
directions: Rinse shrimp and scallops.
Slice mushrooms.
In 12-inch hot skillet, melt margarine.
Cook shrimp and scallops, stirring, about 5 minutes, just until done.
Remove to a bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon of margarine to skillet.
Add mushrooms and sherry. Cook, stirring, until mushrooms are tender.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix the salad oil, vinegar, Worcestershire, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper; pour over drained beans.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Remove garlic before serving.

title: cube steak and onion gravy
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in oil.
Remove onion; set aside.

On wax paper, mix salt, pepper and about 1/4 cup flour. Sprinkle steak seasoning on steaks and lightly flour; with skillet over medium heat, brown steaks for about 5 minutes on each side. Remove steaks.
Brown remaining flour.
Add water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onions and steak; simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve steak topped with onions and gravy.

title: no fail microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk; stir until partially blended.
Place butter in the center of mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir until creamy and smooth.
Blend in nuts; pour into buttered 8-inch pan and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: chili sauce
directions: Tie pickling spice in a bag.
Peel tomatoes.
Cut up in chunks. Dice onions and celery.
Add all these to rest of ingredients. Cook over low heat 2 hours.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: waffles
directions: Sift
flour, then measure.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar to
the flour, then sift all together in a medium bowl. In another bowl, mix liquid ingredients and then combine them with the
dry
ingredients.
Mix
just
enough to blend only. Preheat a
waffle
baker
in
closed position on dark or high setting before each use.
When light goes out, pour 5/8 cup of batter
in waffle
baker and immediately close cover.
Bake 5 minutes
or until
waffle is golden brown.
Wait until signal light goes out before making successive waffles.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Cut crust from bread and cut each slice into fine strips.
Place over top of peaches.
Mix sugar, egg, flour and margarine.
Pour over bread strips.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients together, adding beaten eggs last.
Pour mixture into hot skillet with melted butter and stir until heated through.
Place skillet in 350° oven.
When crusted around and on top, stir and let the crust form again.
Do this twice, allowing the last to remain on sides and top.
This takes about 40 minutes.
Serve in squares plain or with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Soften onion in fat.
Cook beef in fat with onion until red is gone.
Remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and cook 30 minutes.
Add whole corn.
Put in baking dish.
Mix corn bread mix and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 400° until corn bread is done.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Pour 1 1/2 c. boiling water with oatmeal and stir. Cool. Cream together butter and sugars. Add eggs, cooled oats, and beat well. Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Spread in a greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 3501 for 25 minutes. Test for doneness. Make frosting and spread while warm.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift in mixing bowl flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add the oil, vanilla, vinegar and water.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and salad oil to boiling point; pour immediately over chopped vegetables.
Add salt, pepper and lots of celery seed to taste.
Let stand at least overnight (the longer, the better).
It improves with age.
Keep in covered jar or bowl in refrigerator.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 1-crust pie in 9-inch pie pan.
Cream margarine.
Gradually add brown sugar; cream well.
Blend in corn syrup and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add slightly beaten eggs and chopped pecans.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Dice up eggplant.
Add salt and pepper. Add croutons on top of eggplant.
Place a good layer of Mozzarella and Parmesan on, then top with sliced tomatoes, salt and pepper. Place bacon over to cover the tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and milk. Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and milk well blended. Beat in confectioners sugar and vanilla.

title: p. s.  i love you!!!(frozen drink)
directions: Blend together to desired consistency.
Sit back and enjoy! This is delicious!!!

title: chicken and beer
directions: Put cut up chicken and sliced onion in pan.
Let cook for 30 minutes.
Add beer, spices, salt and pepper.
Cook for 30 minutes more at 375°.

title: picante chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken, skin if desired.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over chicken.
Pour picante sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour (or until chicken is done).

title: herb chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Put in a slice of Swiss cheese on each.
Combine cream of chicken soup with wine.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle one cup stuffing on top and drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken and ham bake
directions: Cook mushrooms, onion, peppers, garlic and thyme in butter until tender.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
You may sprinkle shredded cheese over the top when almost done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gazpacho mold
directions: In large bowl dissolve gelatin in 2 cups tomato juice.
Heat remaining juice and add to gelatin mixture.
Add veggies and place in greased 5 cup mold.

title: bean and bacon slaw
directions: Stir 1 tablespoon vinegar into 1/2 cup mayonnaise; add 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar; pour this mixture over slaw.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix and pour into two (9-inch) cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot loaf
directions: Soak apricots in water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mix egg with sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together alternately with orange juice and water mixture.
Add nuts and apricots and blend well.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours in a 350° preheated oven.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: french toast(low-fat)
directions: In a shallow pan or bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.

In a nonstick skillet, over medium heat in liquid Butter Buds, place the pieces of bread after they have been dipped in the Egg Beater mixture. Brown about 3 minutes on each side. Add more liquid Butter Buds, if needed.
Serve with lite maple syrup.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in heavy large pan.
Cook to 300° or hard-crack stage, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay chocolate candy on top and spread as it melts.
Sprinkle on pecans, cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: honey mustard baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
In a saucepan, melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients and heat through.
Brush glaze over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is golden brown, basting chicken frequently with glaze while baking.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Put Hershey bar in a saucepan and melt, stirring constantly. Allow to cool. Stir into the Cool Whip.
Pour into the pie crust. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Pie is ready to serve.

title: beef cubed steaks
directions: Combine garlic, basil and pepper.
Divide mixture in half. Press half of the seasoning mixture evenly into both sides of steaks.
Heat oil and remaining seasoning mixture in large nonstick frying pan over medium heat.
Add zucchini; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Continue cooking 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Remove vegetables to warm platter.
Increase heat to medium high.
Parboil steaks 3 to 4 minutes, turning once. Season steaks with salt if desired.
Garnish vegetables with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken pieces in boiling water until tender; let cool. Remove bones and skin; cut into bite size pieces.
Combine stuffing mix, sage and onion.
Combine soups and milk in a saucepan; cook until hot.
Pour half the soup mixture over stuffing; stir to moisten.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken pieces on top; cover with remainder of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Bake cake in 3 layers.
Put 1 cake layer in a punch bowl, a layer of pudding, a layer of Cool Whip and a can of pie filling.
Repeat process for second and third layers.
Will fill punch bowl to top.

title: veggie dip
directions: Chop into small pieces the broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper and tomatoes. Mix the mayo, cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch together. Mix until smooth (about 20 minutes). Combine all ingredients. Store in refrigerator. Serve on Ritz crackers or hot crescent rolls.

title: mom's sweet potato cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar; add egg yolks and beat well.
Blend in hot
water,
dry
ingredients, potatoes, nuts and vanilla. Beat egg
whites;
fold	into
batter.
Pour
in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach soup
directions: Boil chicken broth and add bouillon cubes.
Roll ground beef into mini meat balls and add to boiling broth.
When meat is cooked, add frozen spinach.
When spinach is cooked, beat eggs and cheese and pour into soup.
Stir and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Total cooking time is 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: I use my food processor to mix all of the ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator, then roll in pecans.

title: terri douglass'  paella valenciana(makes 8 servings)
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
In Dutch oven or heavy kettle, brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken.
Pour off fat.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in rice, broth and next five seasonings.
Add chicken.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Gently stir in shrimp, fish, lobster and peas.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Carefully stir in artichoke hearts and pimientos.
Heat through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into chunks.
Put into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup together and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed; sprinkle over top of soup mixture.
Melt oleo and pour over top of crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cabbage spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, pepper and spices until done.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Let simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: good and good for you spinach salad
directions: Divide spinach, orange slices and mushrooms among 4 plates. Combine remaining ingredients in a cruet and shake well. Serve over salad. You can also add cooked bacon pieces.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and break the spinach in pieces.
Chop the spring onions or thinly slice the red onion.
Fry, drain and chop the bacon. Chop the eggs.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with following topping which has been mixed together.

title: nora's english trifle
directions: Make Jell-O by package instructions.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add pound cake and sprinkle with sherry; stir and refrigerate until firm.
Make custard by box instructions. Refrigerate until cold.
In a glass tall sided bowl, pour in Jell-O mixture.
Cover with custard; top with whipped cream and place strawberries last of all.

title: make-your-own personal pizza
directions: Put each biscuit into a 3-inch circle on a greased baking sheet.
Mix oregano with spaghetti or pizza sauce.
Spread some on each biscuit.
Top with cheese and any other toppings you like. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Let come to a boil the sugar, butter and milk, then add vanilla.
Mix together coconut, cocoa and oatmeal.
Stir into hot mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Cool.

title: impossible dream pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix for 2 minutes.
Or put all in mixing bowl and use a mixer for 4 minutes.
Put mixture into a 10-inch (has to be 10-inch) greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Mix everything together, and add meat.
Shape into 6 loaves, and place in greased shallow pan.
Bake in oven 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add ribbon of catsup before serving.

title: cranberry baked beans
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Combine beans, bacon, brown sugar and cranberries.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 2 hours. Enjoy!

title: salmon mold
directions: Mix salmon and cream cheese first; add other ingredients and shape into a ball; chill for 4 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix accordingly and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: potato broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli until tender.
Put potatoes, broccoli, sour cream and seasonings in food processor and blend. Eat as is or put in baking dish to reheat.
Good, healthy and green!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli.
Put in a bowl and add the next 5 ingredients.
In bottom of casserole dish, melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Pour broccoli mixture into casserole.

title: chocolate philly fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to cream cheese, mixing well until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
(If using premelted canned chocolate, you may use more if you like dark chocolate fudge.)
Spread mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Reserve small amount of bread crumbs and cheese for topping.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done.
Bone chicken and add to broth, butter, salt, pepper and soup mix.
Add remaining ingredients and boil until noodles and vegetables are done.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix together in large coffee pot or crock-pot.
Heat.
Enjoy.

title: lasagna reno
directions: Remove sausage from casing and chop.
In a Dutch oven, over medium heat, saute sausage, onion and garlic, stirring frequently, until well browned, around 15 minutes.

title: jerky turkey burgers with mango sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixing well. Chill until ready to use.

title: 7 minute cake icing
directions: Mix together in double boiler. Beat for 7 minutes. Should be thick like melted marshmallows.
If not, cook longer.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken.
Fry in hot oil as for serving. Remove from frypan and drain.
Make a dark roux with drippings and flour (add flour to drippings in pan and stir constantly until dark brown - it will smell a little burned).
Add onion and garlic. Cook until soft.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and water.
Cook until sauce is smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place chicken in bottom of 4 1/2 to 5-quart Dutch oven and pour sauce on top (chicken can be deboned if you prefer).
Cook slowly on top of stove for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
If sauce gets too thick, a little water may be added.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: baked pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slightly beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining filling ingredients, except nuts, until well blended. Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until filling is set and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pie plate on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings. Serve warm or at room temperature with whipped cream.

title: collector's cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll pastry to 12-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Place in 9-inch pie plate.
Turn under edges. Melt caramels with water in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently until smooth.
Spoon sliced apples into crust.
Top with caramel sauce.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon with margarine until mixture crinkles.
Sprinkle this and walnuts over apples. Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Wash and slice squash into small slices.
Cover and boil until tender; drain well.
Reserve 1 cup cooked squash.
Blend cornmeal, onion and egg together.
Add to remaining squash.
Place carefully into hot grease by teaspoon.
Cook until brown, turning only once.
Drain onto paper towel and enjoy while hot.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown venison and chopped onion.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Mash pears.
Heat pear juice and add jello.
Cook until syrupy.
Mix cream cheese with milk and add pears.
Mix in jello and add Cool Whip.
Congeal in oblong Pyrex dish.

title: crunch cauliflower salad
directions: Wash vegetables well.
Break cauliflower into flowerets. Combine with radishes, onions and chestnuts in a medium mixing bowl.
Toss gently.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and milk.
Sift together 1/2 of the flour with salt and baking powder.
Beat until smooth and add only as much more flour as needed.
Batter should be thin enough to run through a funnel.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix water, rice and onion soup mix.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix together cream of chicken and celery.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine soups, broth and tomatoes; blend until smooth.
Layer the tortillas, chicken, onion, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: low-fat banana milkshakes
directions: Mix all ingredients on high setting in a blender until mixture is creamy.
Serve cold.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold gently into buttermilk mixture and pour into 2 (9-inch) deep dish pie shells.
Bake in 325° oven until brown and set.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix well.
Marinate chicken 1 hour.
Cook chicken on grill over low coals, turning every 5 to 10 minutes.
Dip in marinade with each turn.

title: wine cooler
directions: Put sugar and water in a pitcher and stir until dissolved. Add the orange juice and ice. Fill with chilled red wine.

title: jean bon zetty
directions: Boil pork and chicken separately and save broth.
Cool, debone and dice.
Cook noodles and drain.
Boil celery and onion in small amount of water; do not drain.
Combine all ingredients except cheese, including broth in a large pan and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serve with cheese.

title: wonder brownies
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, until done.

title: angels on horseback(method:  stick)
directions: Poke a hole in the end of a strip of bacon, then begin to wind the bacon around the stick upward.
Toast over the open coals.

title: beef and mashed potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, add chopped bell pepper, garlic, basil, salt, mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 25 minutes. Place in casserole dish.
Combine mashed potatoes, parmesan cheese and parsley.
Place on top of the ground beef mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are heated (about 10 minutes).
Serves 4-6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in bowl and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Mix well. Stir in beaten eggs. Mix in raisins and walnuts (nuts are optional). Mix in flour. Pour batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Top with a sprinkle of brown or confectioners sugar. (I prefer brown.) Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: muffin pan meat loaves
directions: Combine tomato sauce, stuffing mix, egg, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Spoon mixture into 18 greased muffin cups.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and dry mustard. Spread over top of meat loaves.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or freeze.
These are great to have in the freezer when you're in a hurry.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and water and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Turn out on floured surface and knead for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut out.
Place in greased pan and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes. These will keep in refrigerator 7 to 10 days to be used as needed.

title: beef taco casserole
directions: Cook beef until slightly brown; stir in taco mix, tomato paste and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir occasionally. Cook macaroni. Stir corn and 1 cup of the cheese into meat mixture; pour into 2-quart buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with the rest of the cheese. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Mix the 3/4 cup water with the sugar.

Heat and while waiting for this to come to a boil, mix the cornstarch, salt, 1/4 cup water and lemon juice. Boil together until mixture is clear and then add the jello. Stir well to dissolve jello, then cool. Add the fresh raspberries.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Add vegetables on top of chicken.
Mix together both cans of soup with one can of chicken broth.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix together flour, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over soup.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together

eggs, melted margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla. After mixing, divide into 2 pie shells. Let cool in refrigerator 3 hours. Put on drained pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip. Place cherries on top of Cool Whip; sprinkle on nuts and drizzle chocolate. Best to refrigerate overnight.

title: sugarless chocolate pie
directions: Mix honey, peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put into an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate. While mixing pudding, slice the banana into crust and add pudding. Chill. Can add whipped topping when serving.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Separate flowerets from stems and place in a small saucepan with water.
Cut up stems.
Melt the butter and saute the onion, garlic, salt, pepper and cut up broccoli.
Add the broth and cook for 30 minutes.
Puree and return to pot.
Thicken with flour and water paste.
Stir in cheese.
Meanwhile cook flowerets and stir them in and serve.

title: almond cheese filled coffee cake
directions: Mix yeast, water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add eggs.
Cut butter into flour and salt; mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Divide into 2 balls and roll each into an 8 x 10-inch rectangle.
Make filling by combining cream cheese, almond and 1 cup sugar.
Spread half of the cream cheese filling on each rectangle and fold, by taking each long side toward the middle, making sure the sides overlay a little.
Fold ends up about 1 1/2-inches.
Lay on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake immediately for 25 minutes at 400° to 425°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle a thin glaze over this.

title: dry baking mix
directions: Sift or mix dry ingredients.
Cut in lard until mixture resembles fine meal.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients, except nutmeg.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 325°. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: orange pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a large bowl. Add the egg and mix until fluffy. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Add vanilla, orange rind and chopped pecans.
Mix well. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until finger doesn't leave print in preheated oven at 350°.
May frost with powdered sugar frosting made with powdered sugar and orange juice.

title: shrimp boulettes
directions: Grind first 6 ingredients and mix together with egg, mixing well.
Form balls
using a heaping spoonful of
this mixture. Roll in seasoned flour and fry in about 2-inches of hot oil until golden brown.
I like to use a cast-iron skillet.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounce bag of chocolate chips and spread on top.
Refrigerate until chocolate is firm.
Cut into squares.

title: banana topping
directions: Cook bananas and sugar until clear.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Remove from heat and stir.
Put on cake.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: In a bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and milk.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Roll out between waxed paper into a 12x10 inch rectangle.
Melt chocolate chips; cool slightly.
Spread over dough to with 1/2 inch of edges.
Roll up tightly, like a jelly roll, starting with a long side.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 20-30 minutes or until easy to handle.
Unwrap and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Place on greased baking sheets.

title: mary catherine's chocolate delight
directions: Mix the ingredients and put in ice cream can (1 gallon). Finish filling can with milk and add 5 teaspoons Nestle Quik (liquid) for each 4 cups of milk added.
Follow instructions for your ice cream freezer to make the ice cream.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Kool-Aid and nuts together.
Stir well. Add Cool Whip and mix together.
Chill before serving.

title: easy spinach quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Cook spinach according to package instructions.
Drain and squeeze out moisture.
(Dry spinach will be about the size of your fist.)
Scald cream; cool.
Place in blender with eggs, salt and nutmeg.
Blend until smooth but not frothy.
Place spinach over bottom of pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over and top with cheese.
Bake about 55 minutes at 300° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cocoa peanut butter chip pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Sprinkle chips on bottom of crust. In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Add sweetened condensed milk and water.
Stir with whisk until well-blended. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Pour into crust. Bake 30 minutes or until edges are set.
(Center will firm while cooking.)
Cool slightly.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Muffins, bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix beans, green pepper and onions. Then
mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over the bean mixture. Stir. Pour into a bowl and place into the refrigerator until cooled.

title: chow chow
directions: Combine cucumbers, green pepper, cabbage, onion and tomatoes in a large nonmetal container.
Dissolve salt in 2 quarts water; pour over vegetables.
Cover; let stand 8 to 10 hours.
Drain well.
Cook lima beans, green beans and carrots in 2 cups water for 20 minutes, or until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine all vegetables and remaining ingredients in a Dutch oven; boil 10 minutes.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend all in blender; blend for 3 minutes.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Shake well before serving.
Good in coffee, hot chocolate or over ice cream.
Cheers!

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix the first 11 ingredients and shape into balls.
Brown in the hot fat or in the oven.
Remove meat and stir into the fat the flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Add the water and sour cream. Return meat to gravy. Cook 15 to 20 minutes. Can be left in a crock-pot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Skin and debone chicken and set aside.
Put all remaining ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into a small sauce pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Place chicken in a baking dish and completely cover with the sauce. Bake at 325° F. until meat is tender or about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with sauce over boiled rice.
This sauce is also excellent with lamb or pork.

title: fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients and pour into deep dish pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Seal edges and trim.
Brush with egg white.
Bake for 45 minutes.
(The fruit will shrink as it cooks.)

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, coconut, milk and vanilla.
Add buttermilk.
Bake in pie crust for 1 hour on 350°.

title: veal marsala
directions: Cut veal into 2 or 3-inch pieces.
Mix cheese, flour and pepper.
Brown veal in butter; add mushrooms and brown.
Blend in cheese mixture.
Add beef broth and wine.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Uncover and cook until sauce is desired consistency.
Serves 3.

title: cornmeal gravy
directions: Mix together and cook until brown, leaving out milk.
When brown, add in milk.
Stir until thick and serve over biscuits.

title: spatzle
directions: Stir together flour and salt in a bowl.
Blend egg and milk. Stir into flour mixture.
Place 1/2 the dough in a strainer.
Hold over boiling salted water.
With spatula, press dough through the strainer to form the Spatzle.
Repeat with the remaining dough. Cook and stir 5 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, 1/2 can onions and pimento.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon extract.
Add flour and 7-UP alternately, beating after each addition.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hour or until cake tests done.

title: hurry-up ham "n" noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a skillet over medium heat, melt butter, stir in cream.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add ham, cheese, onions, salt and pepper; heat through.
Drain noodles, add to ham mixture and heat through.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Place cut potatoes and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir mixture together.
Sprinkle the cheese over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with 5 cups skim milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip (use large mixing bowl).
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix in serving dish.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients at least several hours before serving (overnight, if possible).
Salad may be drained and put on lettuce leaf.

title: minted nuts
directions: Cook together the sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook until soft ball forms.
Test in cold water or with candy thermometer.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add peppermint and nuts; stir until each nut is covered and mixture hardens. Drop onto paper, a teaspoonful at a time, to cool.
These can be kept in a tightly covered jar for at least a week and can be frozen indefinitely.

title: leftover ham and potato bake
directions: In a buttered baking dish, layer potatoes, ham and cheese until you layer all of your ingredients.
Pour milk over dish and pat your butter all through your layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients together with fingers.
Form dough into a 1 1/4-inch roll.
Chill.
Slice roll into 1/4-inch slices and arrange on cookie sheets.
Before baking, slices may be brushed with egg whites and sprinkled with sesame seed, poppy seed or chopped nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together and stir.
Chill and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Set aside.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Cool.
Pinch cake into small pieces and put a layer in bottom of punch bowl or 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Put a layer of pudding, pineapple, cherry filling and bananas.
Add whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Garnish with cherries.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar until sugar is completely dissolved.
If mixture feels grainy, keep mixing until smooth.
Add onion juice and mix.
Add oil, little at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Finally, add poppy seed and mix.
Makes 3 1/2 cups. Recipe may be cut in half.

title: mandel bread(cookies)
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and beat.
Then combine with remaining ingredients.
Form 2 loaves and place on greased cookie sheet (use wet hands).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Slice loaves into one-inch pieces, short length across.

title: heavenly pineapple
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and place in saucepan.
Add sugar and flour and beat until smooth.
Add eggs until you get a smooth consistency.
Add salt and stir.
Add water.
Bring to a thick sauce stage.
Add cooked sauce to pineapple.
Add marshmallows and cool until ready to serve.
Add pecans if you want.
Be careful sauce will scorch easily.
Cook on low and stir.

title: cheesy french bread
directions: Split bread lengthwise. Spread with butter, chiles, mayonnaise and cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Slice and serve warm. Delicious!

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Arrange cut up rhubarb (2 to 4 cups) in greased baking dish. Mix other ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over rhubarb. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes; serve warm or cold.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberries and wine.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in pecans; turn into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Stir cream cheese, gradually beating in sour cream.
Spread over jello.
Chill.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt. Stir in milk slowly. Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add a little mixture to beaten egg yolks and boil 1 minute longer. Add butter and vanilla; cool.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add both clam juices, wine, oregano, red pepper flakes, basil and salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add clams and parsley.
Return to a boil and remove from heat.
Cook pasta.
Pour clam sauce over linguini mix.
Can sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: t's peanut brittle
directions: Chop peanuts, then sprinkle with salt and warm in the oven. Mix sugar, syrup and water together, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook over moderate heat until thermometer registers 265° or a small amount of mixture forms a hard ball in cold water. Add butter.
Cook slowly to 290°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in warm nuts and vanilla.
Pour on greased baking pan in thin sheet.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Cut peaches into bite-size chunks.
Drain fruit and add to milk mixture.
Pour 1/2 in each pie crust and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate several hours before stirring.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Fry meat, onions, peppercorns and mushrooms in oil until well done.
Put eggs in small bowl and gently beat.
Scrambled eggs into the meat mixture.
Add soy sauce, then rice, mix well, remove from heat and serve.

title: delicious salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding well, then add other ingredients. Stir well and chill.

title: dream bars
directions: Pour and spread mixture over crust and bake until brown.

title: orange-glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots; drain.
Over low heat, melt butter and stir in flour.
Add orange juice, light brown sugar, salt and cinnamon. Stir constantly until smooth and slightly thickened.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix glaze and carrots.
Makes 2 large servings.

title: quick and easy green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium high and cook for about 10 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in boiler or slow cooker and heat at low temperature for about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.
A cup of cheer to warm your holidays.
The spicy taste of Hot Mulled Cider makes a nice change of pace for holiday parties or a soothing way to relax after an exhausting shopping spree.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix egg whites in with pecans; mix in sugar and cinnamon. Bake for 20 minutes at 300° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: baked apples
directions: Core, peel and slice apples.
Toss in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place in baking dish.
Pour apple juice over apples. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: pizzelles
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Add as much flour as needed to make a smooth thin batter, much like a cake batter.
Pizzelle irons are needed to cook these delicious pastries up.
While still warm, sprinkle confectioners sugar on the top.
Store in an airtight container.
Do not attempt to make these on a day that is too humid.

title: topping for fresh fruit
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Serve over cut up melon, honeydew and seedless grapes.

title: pork chops
directions: Cover each pork chop with a slice of lemon.
Put brown sugar on top of lemons.
Put ketchup on top of brown sugar.
Put 1/2-inch or so water on bottom of pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Make gravy with milk and flour and juices from pan.

title: salsa (red)
directions: Boil tomatoes and jalapeno peppers till you smell the peppers.
When cooked blend tomatoes, peppers, onion, small bunch (8 leaves) cilantro, salt and lemon for flavor.

title: green bean bake
directions: Drain green beans.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over green beans.
Cover with Velveeta cheese slices.
Top with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, place 4 tablespoons in one cup of boiling water.
Top with whipped cream and dash of cinnamon.

title: maple pecan brunch ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in microwave dish to melt.
Chop pecans and mix with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Separate 1 can of biscuits.
Split each biscuit horizontally in half for a total of 16 biscuits.
Place in single layer on round baking stone.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Arrange so biscuits overlap each other, in a circular pattern 2 inches from edge of stone. Separate remaining biscuits and do the same, arranging a second ring of biscuits inside the first ring.
(Should be a 5-inch opening in center.)
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Brush with maple syrup.
Slice and serve.

title: ina's cheese roll
directions: Grate sharp cheese; let stand with cream cheese until soft. Add all ingredients; mix well.
Shape with plastic wrap.
Roll in grated pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, covered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and crumble.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Butter nonstick 12-cup Bundt pan.
Set oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Stir in chips. Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until top is springy to touch.
(Do not overbake.) Cool in pan.
Invert; remove and place on cake dish.
When completely cool, drizzle icing on top.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add all of hamburger. Mix until coated.
Spread onto bun halves to edges.
Broil 10 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt oleo in pot.
Season crawfish tails with onion and garlic powder.
Add paprika to oleo.
Saute tails about 7 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic to the pot and add 2 cups water and tomato sauce.
Stir and simmer slowly, about 30 minutes.
Add more seasoning, if necessary.
Add mixture of cornstarch and water slowly until thickened.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: june's chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheddar-pecan cheese ball
directions: Bring Cheddar cheese and cream cheese to room temperature. In medium mixing bowl beat cheeses, sour cream, mustard, and onion powder with an electric mixer on medium speed till well combined. Seal and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Shape the cheese mixture into a ball about 4 inches wide and 23/4 inches high. Arrange pecan halves around base of cheese ball. Coat ball with chopped pecans. Can be refrigerated up to 1 week. For easy spreading, let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving. Makes 1 ball about 2 1/3 cups. (I omit the pecans because I don't care for them and this is still delicious.)

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute over low heat in the butter the onion, carrot and celery until soft.
Add the flour and cornstarch and cook until it just begins to brown.
Add chicken stock; stir until smooth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk; heat.
Add cheese and baking soda.
Heat soup, but try not to boil.
Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
This freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend all together on medium-high speed for about 10 to 15 minutes to make smooth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: fudgy brownies(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Stir in chocolate morsels (optional). Spoon batter into a 9 x 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.
Contains 5 gm of fat per serving when morsels are used.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda; mix.
Add chips and nuts; mix well.
Form into small balls; flatten slightly. Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 310° for 15 minutes.
Different but good.

title: the state cookie of texas
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter, margarine and sugars. Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy. In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats. Add to creamed mixture and mix until blended. Stir in chocolate chunks, pecans and coconut. Line Texas-shaped cookie pan with aluminum foil. Spread cookie dough over whole pan, pressing to flatten to about 1/2-inch thick. Bake in a 350° oven for 22 to 28 minutes. (The top of the cookie will be slightly soft and moist, but will finish baking while still in the pan.) Allow to set in pan for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan, lifting out with help of foil. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Decorate as desired. Makes 1 Texas cookie.

title: hotel roanoke's spoon bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and sugar together.
Scald with boiling water.
Add melted butter.
Beat eggs, then add milk to eggs.
Put two mixtures together.
Add baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pesto and tomato crostini
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place bread on ungreased cookie sheet. Spread each slice of bread with a scant tablespoon of the pesto. Top with tomatoes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake about 8 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted. Makes 12 appetizers.

title: cafe international's chicken sicilian
directions: Dredge chicken strips in flour.
Fry in deep fryer.
Drain. Saute the garlic in heated olive oil until it softens.
Add chicken, mushrooms, peppers, potato and seasonings.
Heat until warm.
Add brine from the cherry peppers jar, about 2 teaspoons. Add tomatoes and olives.
Heat until warm.
Serves 1.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: crazy crust
directions: Lightly grease and flour bottom and sides of 9-inch metal or 10-inch glass pie pan.
Combine all ingredients in medium bowl. Stir until blended, 60 to 70 strokes.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Spread batter thinly on bottom and thickly up sides to within 1/4-inch of rim.
Refrigerate, covered, up to 12 hours before filling and baking.

title: jan's marinated tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle
onions,
parsley
and
garlic
over tomatoes. Make dressing
of the 5 remaining ingredients.
Shake well and pour over
tomatoes.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight, spooning dressing over tomatoes several times.

title: dieter's salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in small jar.
Store in refrigerator. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cooked cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in a pot with water, about 8 to 10 minutes. Lift carefully from pot to a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour melted margarine over cauliflower; sprinkle salt and pepper.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Heat chicken stock to nearly boiling point and add the first seven ingredients.
Boil covered, for a half hour, over medium/low heat, stirring occasionally.
When cabbage and carrots are soft, mix the corn flour with cold water and combine with soup, stirring constantly.
Beat egg whites and add to soup using a swirling motion.
Wait until egg whites are fluffy and floating atop the soup, then your soup is ready.

title: pan tollhouse cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 12-inch round pan. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: black cherry congealed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream.
Congeal 1/2 of the mixture. Cover with sour cream and pour remaining mixture on top. Congeal.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, raisins and nuts.
Mix other ingredients and add apple mixture to batter.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: gateau(swiss pound cake)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder, lemon peel, raisins and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done in greased loaf pan.
Light and delicious!

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken almost done.
Drain and save liquid for stock. Bone when cooled.
Cook frozen broccoli almost done.
Make sauce of mayo, soup, lemon juice and curry.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to recipe directions.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: dad's pickled beets
directions: This is brine covering for canning beets.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Melt the butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in the flour until smooth, then add the milk gradually and stir over low heat until thick.
Drain the salmon; remove bones and skin and flake with a fork.
Add cream sauce, mushrooms, celery, onion, parsley, mustard, cream, salt and pepper.
Separate the eggs and stir the unbeaten yolks into the fish mixture.
Beat the whites stiff and fold in gently.

title: sunset yogurt salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup and chill until slightly thickened. Blend in yogurt and pour into 5-cup bowl.
Chill until set, but not firm.

Add cold water to remaining gelatin, then add pineapple with juice and carrots. Chill until slightly thickened and spoon over gelatin mixture in bowl. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours. Serve with crisp salad greens and carrot curls, if desired.

title: senior breakfast hot dish(impossible ham and cheese pie)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking pan or dish. Spread ham, cheese and onions in bottom of pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds with blender or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pan.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries and place in a 3-quart glass casserole.
Add sugar and orange juice.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture boils and berries pop.
Let stand, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cheese biscuits(my mother's way)
directions: Mix cheese and margarine until blended well.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
(Do not roll out to make biscuits.)
I use a spatula or with a knife I "flick" out on ungreased pan in bite-size pieces.
Bake at 325° for approximately 12 minutes.
If overbaked, the flavor will change.
Makes approximately 400 biscuits.

title: microwave vegetable beef casserole
directions: Crumble beef into 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir in squash, onion, tomatoes, rice, soy sauce, basil and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and microwave on High for 27 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir frequently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kris kringle cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together and chill.
Roll out 3/8-inch thick and cut with favorite cookie cutter.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes (use greased or nonstick cookie sheet).
Cool.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine pie filling and orange peel in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chilled strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites at room temperature until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Spread mixture into buttered 10-inch pie plate, spreading sides slightly higher.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool shell completely. Beat cream until foamy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold in berries.
Spread mixture evenly into pie shell.
Chill about 3 hours before serving.
Makes 1 pie. Similar to Strawberry Fluff at Cheese Barn.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla. Beat well,
then
add egg and beat again real well.
Then add flour, salt and
soda, beat until well blended.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.
Roll
dough
in
little
balls
and dip in sugar;
press down in cookies with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: big game lasagna
directions: Brown the meat and sausage in a large pot or deep frying pan. Add the onions, celery and carrots, then saute on medium heat until tender.
Add the tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer about 1 hour.
Bring the water to boil; add olive oil and cook the noodles until tender and pliable (do not overcook or it gets hard to handle).
Remove from heat and immerse in cold water to stop the cooking process; lay them out on a towel to drain completely.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Chill mixture until begins to thicken.
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Blend well.
Pour into a dish or mold and chill until firm.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Combine mix and oil.
Add spices.
Pour over crackers.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chombotha
directions: Saute sausage, mushrooms, onion and pepper with all seasonings. Add tomatoes and 2 cans of water.
Place in a soup pan.
Add potatoes and string beans, diced and sliced as desired.
Simmer until tender.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion.
Add corn, water, seasoning and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and heat to serve.

title: ranch noodles and turkey
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In a skillet melt 1/2 cup butter and add dressing mix.
Add frozen peas and carrots; heat thoroughly. Toss with noodles and add turkey or chicken.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until done.
Cool and spread Marshmallow Creme over cooled brownies.
In small saucepan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal.
Spread over Marshmallow layer.
Chill and cut into squares.
Store in fridge.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: Cook milk and dates in double boiler until thick.
Add pecans and stir.
Put on salty side of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and add icing.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix ingredients and put in freezer.
Stir every 2 hours.
Makes a little over a gallon.

title: sweet sour chicken(gets raves everytime)
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts and place into casserole dish. Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup mix together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 370°.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes longer.
Serve over pasta.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Cool.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions.
Crumble cake into large pieces.
In a large bowl, layer the following ingredients:
1/2 crumbled cake, 1/2 pudding mix, 1 can cherry pie filling and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.
Repeat for second layer.
Decorate with toasted pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Distribute ingredients evenly in a large oblong ungreased cake pan, one on top of the other; do not mix.
Pour can of pineapple with juice into pan.
Place coconut on top.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix. Slice butter into small pats and arrange over all.
Push pecans into mix to center.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown. Top with whipped cream.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Cut up in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and onions over sausage.
Next add a layer of pepperoni, a layer of cottage cheese, then a layer of New York cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Brown sausage. Drain and add all ingredients. Simmer for about 45 minutes or until tender. Delicious served with rice or salad and bread.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Add a pound of ground beef (or chuck) and sauteed onion to ingredients. Simmer.

title: toffee
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy frying pan.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 20 minutes.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin small pieces.
Place in a deep dish.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add to sweet potatoes along with water, salt and nutmeg.
Cut butter in pieces and lay over ingredients.
Cover with favorite pastry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until crust is brown.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together.
Shape into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Cover with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup catsup.
Return to oven and bake about 20 minutes longer.

title: natchez cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Arrange crackers side by side in pan.
Stir butter and sugar together in pan until sugar melts.
Mix in vanilla. Increase heat and boil 1 minute.
Pour over crackers.
Top with nuts and bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips on top.
Cool 4 minutes.
Cut along crackers to separate.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except wieners.
Dip wieners in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, sugar and boiling water in bowl.
Allow to cool; make sure totally cooled.
Add yeast.
Add egg and stir. Add sifted flour and stir.
Chill 2 to 4 hours in refrigerator. Shape into individual rolls and cover.
Allow to rise, doubling in bulge, approximately 2 hours.
Bake at 425°.

title: texas spoon bread
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk to 180°; stir in cornmeal.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, sugar, salt and baking powder.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks; return all to pan and mix well.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form and fold into hot mixture until well blended.
Pour into 8-inch greased baking dishes or divide into 6 French white individual bowls.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or large bowl for 30 minutes or less for smaller bowls or until well puffed and golden.
Use spoon to serve.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients, saving some cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep chocolate cake
directions: Place oil, water and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Add flour, sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add salt, egg and vanilla; mix well. Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Frost or sprinkle with confectioners sugar or serve with whipped cream.

title: fruit pie(blackberry, strawberry or peach)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Stir in Jell-O until thoroughly dissolved.
Let cool.
Pour over fresh fruit in cooked pie shells.
Cover with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Makes enough for about 1 1/4 cups, serving for two.

title: shrimp louisianne
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Saute vegetables.
Add raw, peeled shrimp and saute a few minutes longer.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder.
Add milk gradually and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add catsup and parsley.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice with green salad and French bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese barbecue pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch thick strips.
Mix the last 4 ingredients and soak the pork in it.
Spread the pork in a baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Baking pan should be dry and pork fat starting to come out.

title: hamburger noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add onion and soup.
Heat and let simmer 30 minutes.
Boil noodles to taste and mix with hamburger sauce.

title: pineapple chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken with flour mixed with salt and spices.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Remove chicken to casserole; set skillet aside. Mix sugar and cornstarch in small pan; stir in soy sauce and syrup drained from pineapple.
Cook, stirring until sauce is thick and clear.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for "filled" one-crust pie, using 9-inch pie pan. Flute as desired. In medium bowl (I use wire whisk), stir eggs (1 at a time), corn syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust-lined pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Make Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Add box of peas while Rice-A-Roni is in last 15 minutes of cooking.
Let mixture completely cool.
Add water chestnuts (chopped).
Add artichoke hearts, cut into 1/4.
Add olives.
Add nuts (optional).
Add mayonnaise.
Mix well and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 12 medium muffin cups.

title: hot spiced cranberry cider
directions: In a large pot, combine apple cider, cranberry juice, brown sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves and lemon slices. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. With a slotted spoon, remove cinnamon, cloves and lemon slices. Serve hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into graham cracker crust (or chocolate). Refrigerate.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking powder in a large
bowl.
Add
shortening,
sugar,
eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in oats and raisins. Put 1 heaping
teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cut-outs
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Add and mix well.
Chill dough. Roll on floured surface.
Flour cookie cutter and rolling pin. Bake at 375° on lightly greased cookie sheet until light brown (about 7 minutes).
Cool; frost with Frosting for Sugar Cookies.

title: hot muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Drop into lined muffin tin and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and mix with taco seasoning as directed on package. Add beans and both jars of taco sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 30 minutes or longer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms by wiping with a damp paper towel.
Remove stems and save.
Place about 2 tablespoons of the olive oil in shallow baking dish.
Place mushrooms, hollow side up, in dish. Drizzle a bit of olive oil in each cap.

title: fried apple jacks
directions: Barely cover apples with water and stew 15 minutes.
Take off heat and let sit 15 minutes.
Drain and add ingredients.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 300° and let cool.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Twenty minutes before serving, mix together half of orange sherbet and the unsweetened pineapple juice.
After 20 minutes, stir in orange soda and 7-Up.
Then drop by spoonfuls the rest of the sherbet.
It will float!

title: turkey or chicken and dressing
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Soak oatmeal in milk overnight.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in water.
Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: teriyaki
directions: Mix together.
Cut up a 3 to 4 pound beef roast into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Pour teriyaki sauce over meat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Cook on grill.

title: rice chex mix(microwave)
directions: Place Rice Chex and pecans in a brown grocery sack.
Mix together in microwave bowl the brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Microwave 4 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir well. Will foam and be light in color.
Pour over mixture in bag. Shake, microwave 1 minute.
Shake, microwave 1 minute.
Shake, pour out on cookie sheets to cool.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour. Add nuts and bake in spouted pan at 350° until done.
Remove from pan and while warm, pour glaze over cake.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: lemon poppy-seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into two large greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes before removing from pans.
Can be frozen.

title: fancy potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes 1/2-inch thick and boil.
Put in Pyrex dish. Mix all ingredients together and heat until you can stir.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, unbeaten eggs and vanilla. Let stand for shortening to soften slightly.
Sift flour once. Measure and sift onto waxed paper or into another bowl with salt, soda, spices and cocoa. Scoop up with sifter and sift 2 or 3 times to mix ingredients.

title: goulash
directions: In a large skillet, brown together the ground beef and onion. Season with garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add tomatoes. Cook the macaroni in salt water until tender.
Drain and add to meat mixture; simmer on low for 15 minutes.
Pour into individual bowls.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: orange roughy parmesan
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Spread this mixture over fish after it has been put in shallow pan.
Cover with foil; put under broiler for 12 minutes.
Remove foil and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Mix together in order given.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: shake and bake chicken coating
directions: Mix ingredients well. Bake chicken at 350° for about 1 hour. Makes several servings. May be stored in jar indefinitely.

title: smothered steak(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then turn to low for 8 hours or high for 5 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: light 'n crisp waffles
directions: Preheat waffle maker.
Mix all but egg whites in a large bowl.
Beat on low until moistened.
Increase to medium, and mix until smooth.
By hand, gently fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/2 c. batter over grids.
Close waffle maker.
Bake until golden, 2-1/2 to 3 minutes.
Repeat.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into an airtight container.

title: rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, heat first 4 ingredients until boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until milk is almost gone and rice is tender. Stir in vanilla. Raisins can be added with vanilla.

title: kugelhupf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl.
Add milk, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, butter, eggs, vanilla and 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat on low speed, scrapping bowl occasionally.
Stir in raisins, lemon peel and remaining flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy corn puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 5-cup souffle dish or 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Cook corn as directed on package; drain.
Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and salt with hand beater until smooth. Stir in corn and cheese.
Pour into souffle dish.
Bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Chop jalapenos and mix with all other ingredients.
Place in a greased cast iron skillet and bake at 425 degrees for about 30 min.

title: potato soup with sausage
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and apple and cook 5 minutes.
Add cabbage; cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in chicken broth, potatoes, carrots and seasonings.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Add thinly sliced sausage and zucchini.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until potatoes and vegetables are tender.
This recipe makes 10 cups.

title: gumbo joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Add soup and rinse can with water, adding to hamburger.
Heat while stirring over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Serve with buns.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to mixture with buttermilk.
Blend well. Stir in pecans, cherries and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool a few minutes and remove from pans.

title: mango butter
directions: Add water to mangoes and cook until soft enough to mash. Press through a sieve if the mangoes are stringy.
Add sugar and spices.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes or until thick.
Stir frequently to prevent burning.
Pour into hot sterile glasses and seal with paraffin.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt
margarine
over
low
heat.
Add	chocolate. Stir until just
melted.
Remove
from heat. Stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine with cream cheese. Beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread in lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate
until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.
(I use walnuts.)

title: deep dish microwave brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes (may take 1 to 3 minutes longer, depending on microwave).
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Saute pork or bacon.
Remove when soft or crisp.
Save 1 to 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onion, pepper and celery; saute until golden brown.
