Add carrots, potatoes and water and salt.
Simmer until almost tender.
Add the hard part of clams and juice.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Add chopped soft part of clams, thyme and tomatoes.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease three loaf pans and divide batter evenly.
Bake at 350°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mixed fruit soup
directions: Wash dried fruit and soak in cold water 1/2 hour.
Add cinnamon stick, lemon slices, tapioca and sugar.
Simmer, covered, until almost tender (about 10 minutes), stirring occasionally. Stir in raisins and apple slices and cook a little longer.
Taste soup; if you wish a stronger flavor, add more sugar and/or lemon juice or add 2 tablespoons fruit syrup or grape juice.

title: chocolate buckeyes
directions: *Or use 1 pound chocolate melts.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make 3 holes.
Put oil in one, vinegar in one, and vanilla in one.
Pour cold water over this and mix well.	Bake in a greased 9 by 13 inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: acini fruit salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Cool.
Drain juice from all fruit and reserve.
Cook juice, flour and eggs until thick to make custard. Pour custard over pasta and let set like pudding (2 hours), then add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: marble brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in margarine until like cornmeal.
Add milk, vanilla and peel.
Stir with fork.
Gather into ball and work with hands to form a pliant dough. Shape into rectangle 7 x 2 x 1-inches. Wrap in wax paper and chill for 1 hour.
Slice 1/8-inch thick. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: auntie's chili
directions: Drain beans into colander.
Rinse well.
Cook meat until done, then sear it in skillet.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix peaches and lemon juice.
Stir together the sugar, flour and cinnamon; mix with peaches.
Turn into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute. Cover edge with strips of foil to prevent excessive browning. Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: stir-fry beef and noodles
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef; cook and stir just until tender.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, onion, garlic, capers and bouillon.
Cook and stir just until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Add wine; cook 1 minute.
Keep warm.
Prepare Creamettes egg noodles as package directs; drain.
Serve meat mixture over hot cooked noodles.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all the ingredients well. Spread in buttered 9 x
13-inch pan. Spread 1 large package chocolate chips, melted over peanut butter layer. Chill for 30 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer each ingredient.
Sprinkle a little sugar (or substitute) on each layer if desired.
On top, put 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Do not mix until serving time.
Let "set" in fridge until ready to serve.

title: scratch cheese cake
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese, vanilla and lemon juice together well, then pour into prepared crust and refrigerate.
Serve with cherry pie filling for cherry cheese cake or my personal favorite is to serve with strawberry pie filling over the chilled cheese cake.

title: torte elysee
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt until thick and lemon colored. Fold in sifted flour and baking powder alternately with the 6 stiffly beaten egg whites, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into two (2) buttered and floured layer cake pans.
Spread over layers a meringue made by beating 4 egg whites until stiff and folding in 4 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle one layer with shredded blanched almonds, the other with coconut.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 30 minutes.
Spread whipped cream between layers and around sides of cake.
Sprinkle sides with shredded, blanched almonds, browned in butter.

title: anna biehn's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; peel when warm.
Dice cooked potatoes. Add all other ingredients and stir until mixed well.
If too dry, add milk to obtain smoother consistency or to your liking.
Serves approximately 25 people.
Keeps in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: bread sticks
directions: If using frozen dough, thaw dough but do not let it rise. Spread dough out on large, lightly greased cookie sheet.
Pour margarine over dough and spread around to cover dough.
Sprinkle seeds and bouillon granules over dough.
Cover with the shredded cheese.
Bake at 450 for 15 -20 minutes.
Cut into rectangular pieces with scissors.
Serve hot or cold.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, buttermilk and zucchini.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift and measure flour. Cut in shortening. Add...soda, salt, baking powder, and sugar. Add....yeast mixture and buttermilk. Bake immediately or if you prefer a lighter biscuit, allow to stand for 30 minutes to 2 hours. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: asian chicken salad(makes 1 serving)
directions: Preheat broiler.
Combine soy sauce, lemon juice, sesame oil, garlic and ginger in a small bowl.
Place red pepper and chicken on broiler pan 3-inches from heat.
Broil chicken 3 minutes per side, until opaque.
(May want to put an extra chicken breast on the barbecue and use leftovers.)

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa and salt, then add milk and vanilla. Mix in powdered sugar in 3 parts. Mix until smooth and creamy.

title: candy coated carrots
directions: Cook carrots
until
tender;
drain.
Combine sugar and oleo; stir over
medium
heat until bubbly.
Add Tabasco sauce and salt. Remove
from heat.
Add lemon juice and hot drained carrots. Toss gently until coated evenly.

title: frosted salad
directions: Add 2 cups hot water to both boxes of Jell-O. After dissolved, add 1 1/2 cups cold water. Add fruit and marshmallows; pour in 9 x 13 pan.

title: peanut butter cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar, slowly add milk.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped topping and put into crust; freeze overnight.

title: no-fat added cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place ovenproof pan in oven to heat. Combine ingredients in order above.
Blend well.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: elaine's ratatouille
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in large heavy pan with lid; barely cover with water (or wine, red or white) and simmer until eggplant is tender.
Stir often.
Add tomatoes, chopped with juice (fresh can be used, 2 to 3 large), zucchini, salt, pepper and basil.
Cook slowly to reduced (when it is no longer watery), about 30 minutes.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
Turn into casserole coated with Pam.
Top with several slices of Provolone cheese. Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve as main dish or side dish with meat.

title: bubble and squeak(england)
directions: This recipe uses leftover (or fresh) mashed potatoes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Layer 5 slices of bread in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on top.
Brown sausage and sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on top.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl.
Make another layer of bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour liquid mixture over top of bread. Cover and sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° (uncovered) for 1 hour.
Great for Christmas morning.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a salad bowl; toss gently. Cover; chill thoroughly.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, poppy seeds, mustard and salt in a jar.
Cover tightly; shake vigorously.
Drizzle dressing over salad; toss gently.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: apache bread
directions: Cut top of bread off and set aside.
Pull all of the remaining bread out of the middle.
Mix all ingredients together well and place in the bread.
Replace top on bread.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together in a large, deep pot.
Bring to a steady boil, stirring constantly so it doesn't stick.
Add the peanut butter and then remove from heat.
Once all has been blended evenly, add the cornflakes a little at a time until all flakes are covered.
(Don't use quite as many cornflakes if you like these chewy and not crunchy.)
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet until cooled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar together.
Make a hole in mix.
Add vegetable oil, eggs, cold water and canned pumpkin.
Mix all together and pour into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add optional ingredients to pumpkin bread mixture, if desired.
Also, more spice can be added.

title: stove top lasagne
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet; drain.
Spread 1/2 of spaghetti sauce over meat.
Spread cottage cheese over sauce.
Sprinkle all of noodles over cheese.
Pour remainder of spaghetti sauce over this.

title: 7-up lemon cake(quick cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, frost with lemon icing.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Coat cut up chicken by placing pieces, a few at a time, in a paper bag with flour and desired salt (if any).
Shake.
Brown chicken lightly in oil, then place chicken in large casserole with a tight fitting cover.
Brown rice, garlic and onion in pan in which chicken was browned.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Check occasionally and add water if dry.
One serving is 1/6 recipe with 1/2 cup rice.

title: cajun jambalaya
directions: Put chicken, 5 cups water and 1 teaspoon Cajun seasoning in large pot and boil for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and leave broth in pot.
Debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to broth the soups, sausage, tomatoes, bay leaves and contents of package.
Stir well.
Bring to boil, then turn to low heat and cook, covered, 15 minutes on low heat.
Add chicken and stir well. Cook approximately 20 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Remove bay leaves.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix ingredients together until soft and stiff.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add topping before baking.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cream dry ingredients, then add eggs and cream well.
Add all fruits and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 or 20 minutes at 325°.
Very good at Christmas.
Will keep for weeks.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° until golden brown.
Yields 24 large muffins.

title: 1969 pecan honey cake(greek)
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes to make thin syrup, then add honey and cool.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat; add
corn, onion, picante sauce and cheese. Melt cheese; mix
well.	Add
to
cornbread
mix.
Pour	into greased muffin tins.
Bake	at 475° until brown.
Yield: 10 to 12 muffins. Great with super chili!

title: pan baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in frying pan.
Heat to simmer.
Simmer for 10 or 15 minutes, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
Pour in baking dish and serve.

title: wanda's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for metal pan or 325° for glass pan (Pyrex).
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour.
Nuts are optional.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add dash of salt.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie pan shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° until puffed and brown.

title: passover ice cream
directions: Thaw berries.
Put small amounts of mixed ingredients in a mixer.
Beat at highest speed until thick and fluffy.
As you beat each quantity the mixture should form peaks and reach top of bowl. Continue until entire mixture has been beaten.
Place in 3 or 4 containers, cover tightly and freeze.
Use directly from freezer as any ice cream.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan mix brown sugar and cocoa.
Stir in water.
Add marshmallows; cut into quarters.
Spoon over this the devil's food cake mix made into batter as directed.
Top with broken nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: diet busters
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; melt on low heat and stir.
In separate bowl, combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Spread only 1/2 the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Drizzle caramel over that; dot with reserved cake mixture.
Bake 20 more minutes at 350°.
Let cool before cutting.

title: bread
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add and stir in cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
Combine apples and nuts into mixture. Divide into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until thick; add baking powder and sugar gradually.
Continue beating
until stiff.
Fold in crumbled crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 25 to 30 minutes at 325° until toothpick inserted comes out dry.
Cover with whipped cream 1 hour and 30 minutes before serving.
Or, this can be frozen with or without the topping and keeps very well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup of cold water.
Heat and add jello and sugar to dissolve.
Add cream cheese, broken into pieces. Beat with mixer until stiff.
Add can milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Line pan with crushed graham crackers that have been mixed with melted oleo.
Save small amount of crumbs to sprinkle on top of cake.
Pour cheese mixture into crust-lined pan. Sprinkle crumbs on top and chill before serving.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving juice.
Combine fruits in bowl; mix carefully.
Thin mayonnaise with reserved juice.
Pour over fruits.
Serve on lettuce.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix as per instructions and put into 3 layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Do not refrigerate batter!

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Add 3/4 cup boiling water to jello.
Add other ingredients. When jello mixture starts to gel, add Cool Whip and mix well. Chill until firm.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Add raisins and sugar to water; cook until raisins are plump. Add sour cream and cornstarch.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and add top crust.

title: microwave candy
directions: Melt chips in microwave bowl, approximately 3 minutes at 70%. Remove; stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.
Roll into balls and flatten with sugared bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and shortening. Bake in greased pan at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Beat butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time. Add flour and 7-Up alternately, then add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs with milk and oil.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the drained canned corn to the batter.
Heat shortening or vegetable oil to 375°.
Oil should be 1 inch deep in the kettle.
Drop the batter by spoonfuls into the hot oil.
Cook 1 side until golden brown, then turn to cook other side.
Only turn the fritters once.
Remove from oil when done and place on absorbent paper.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite size pieces in large bowl.
Layer on top the onion, celery, green pepper and peas.
Spread dressing over top.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over evenly.
Add shredded cheese.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Make ahead and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, flour and salt together in a heavy saucepan.
Add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes or until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Let cool a little before pouring into baked pie shell.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Then add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add in layers to batter the nuts, cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a 9 inch pie pan with unbaked dough. Trim edges. Mix peaches, brown sugar, flour, lemon juice, cinnamon and salt together until well combined. Pour into pie shell and dot with butter. Cover pie with top crust and crimp edges. Brush with beaten egg. Bake for 50 mins or so.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Put beef tips in large pan; add water, salt and pepper.
Boil. Dice onion and celery and add to tips.
Also add bouillon cubes. Cook until tender; add water, if necessary.
Put in margarine and rice.
Cook until rice is done.
Minute rice is better!

title: cranberry cocktail
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix cranberry juice and frozen lemonade.
Use your lemonade container and add one container of hot strong tea, 1 container sugar, 1 container water and 1 container liquor.
Float orange slices with mint leaves; more water or ice may be added to suit your taste.

title: hot tuna buns
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, relish, tuna, green peppers, onions, mayonnaise and chopped olives.
Mix well.
Butter hamburger buns, then fill each bun with 1/6 of tuna mixture.
Wrap filled buns in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and buns are nicely warm and slightly crisp.
Serve with fresh steamed vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water or juice.
Let sit.
Then add rest of ingredients.

title: broiled seafood platter
directions: Melt butter in large glass casserole dish.
Crush garlic into butter and stir.
Place mounds of crab meat in middle of glass dish and spoon 2 or 3 spoonfuls of garlic butter over meat.
Place shrimp and scallops in a single layer around the crab meat, turning once to coat with butter.
Squeeze juice of 1 lime over seafood and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil on top rack of oven until shrimp turns pink.
Do not overcook.

title: broccoli rice au gratin
directions: Stir together in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: grandma's tea cakes(has been in my family 75 years)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
flour together, then add flour by
the cup to make dough hard to work.
Roll on floured board as thin or thick as you like; cut with biscuit cutter or shapes. Bake
on
cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until starting to brown.
White-colored are more tender.
Can be
stored in closed container.
If drying occurs, put in 2 or 3 slices of bread; they will absorb the moisture.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble cookies.
Put 1/2 in the bottom of a large dish or pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over cookies. Cover with rest of the cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: stained glass candy
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan and bring to boil. Boil to 300° (hard crack stage) and remove from heat. Add 1 teaspoon flavor and 1 teaspoon color (both must be oil). Be sure to take from fire at exactly 300° or it will become sticky. Pour candy on a foil-lined cookie sheet until hard. Dip in powdered sugar.

title: rosemary squares
directions: Beat eggs vigorously.
Add sugar gradually, then add vanilla and the flour that has been sifted with salt and baking powder into which you have stirred the rosemary.
Fold in nuts and fruits.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs and milk; cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and cool.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 1 hour.
Cool, slice and serve toasted.

title: marshall magic
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sour cream and gelatin.
Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Add pineapple, oranges and nuts.
Fold in nondairy whipped topping.
Transfer to serving dish.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Congeal 1/2 of mixture.
Spread sour cream over top and sprinkle on nuts.
Pour other half of mixture on top and congeal.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together until you can form a roll.
Place in foil and chill well before slicing.
Shape as you place in foil (it's a mess to handle).

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks, honey, yogurt and melted butter together. Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir egg yolk mixture into flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.

title: charlotte's apple pie
directions: Mix margarine and flour until crumbly.
Add cold water 1 tablespoon at a time until mixture is smooth and pliable.
Divide into 2 halves and gently roll out for an 8 or 9-inch pie.
Crust is very thin.

title: vinegar taffy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook to hard ball (260°).
Remove from heat. Stir in soda and vanilla. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan. When cool enough to handle, pull with fingers until light in color.
Pull in long strips about 3/4-inch in diameter. Cut in pieces (1-inch long).
Wrap in wax paper.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Grease jelly roll pan and spread half of the batter in pan.
Spoon 1 can pie filling over batter.
Add the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: elegant german chocolate cake
directions: Drain pineapple well, pressing out excess syrup with back of spoon.
Reserve 1 cup of syrup.
Add chocolate to boiling water; remove from heat to melt.
Cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs until blended.
Beat in chocolate mixture.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat in 1/3 dry ingredients until blended.
Beat in 1/2 reserved pineapple syrup. Repeat, ending with dry ingredients.
Beat batter on medium speed 3 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to complete cooling.
Cut each layer in half through sides to make 4 layers.
Place one layer on cake plate.
Spread with 1/4 Nutty Frosting.
Top with second layer; repeat frosting with remaining 2 layers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spicy dogs
directions: Cook all ingredients together until hot and jelly has melted. Cook on low heat.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and drop from teaspoon into hot fat to fry.
Watch closely and turn to brown other side.
Fry about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Yields 8 to 12 croquettes.

title: crock-pot hamburger soup
directions: Crumble beef into crock-pot (no need to brown).
Add seasonings and soup mix.
Stir in water, tomato sauce and soy sauce; add carrots and celery.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Turn to high.
Add macaroni and cheese.
Cover and cook on high 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves six.
This makes a whole meal with salad and bread.

title: gene's favorite best chip dip ever!
directions: Place ingredients in food processor or mixing bowl.
Mix together thoroughly. Serve with any chip you wish.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix
thoroughly.
Put about two heaping teaspoonfuls in 1 cup of hot water for a delicious hot beverage.

title: brunch pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water; beat 20 strokes.
Turn onto surface well dusted with Bisquick.
Gently roll to coat.
Knead until smooth and no longer sticky, about 60 times.

title: cherry-cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature; whip until fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.

title: saint lucia's crown
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir saffron, milk, sugar, salt, eggs, butter and 2 1/2 c. of the flour into the yeast mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in citron, almonds, lemon peel and remaining flour; enough to make dough easy to handle.

title: carrot muffins with cream cheese filling
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. In separate bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture; stir until moistened.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape in a narrow loaf or spread out on a cookie sheet.
Let set for 8 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Cut in pieces, fry in butter until lightly browned.
Put slices in layers in roaster, spreading each piece with cream of mushroom soup.
Mix remainder of soup with milk to fill can and pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crab cakes with assorted baby greens
directions: Saut scallions and onion in butter.
Combine crab, eggs, mayonnaise, herb, cheese, onions and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Add bread crumbs till mix is holding well enough to make cakes.
Do not make it too dry or too wet.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Make 1 oz. cakes and bread with remaining bread crumbs.
Pan fry in oil till golden brown.
Serve with greens and vinaigrette of your choice.

title: sunday pot roast in slow cooker
directions: This has to be started kind of late Saturday night.
It has to be finished while you attend Sunday school and church services Sunday morning for it to be just right.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in large bowl the chicken, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt, celery, eggs, chicken soup, onion and pimento.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Top with potato chips, almonds and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until the cheese starts to brown and bubble.
Serves 12.

title: zesty artichoke appetizers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serve with toast points or Melba rounds.

title: roll (yeast)
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water.	Heat shortening in milk until melted.
Add
sugar and allow to cool until warm.
Beat in egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour, one cup at a time; knead lightly. Pinch
off	desired
number
of
rolls
and place in greased pan, or	make
loaves.
Allow to double in size in warm place.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lois' aunt jane's dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with potato chips or fresh vegetables.

title: sunday chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Combine all ingredients except rice.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave for 15 minutes. Turn chicken over. Re-cover and microwave 10 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve chicken over the cooked rice.

title: hamburger meat dish
directions: Brown meat; add onion, pepper and celery.
Add cooked noodles, soups, milk and nuts.
Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with crushed potato chips, cheese or whatever you like.
May be frozen.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove and save stems.
Wipe mushroom caps with butter.
Salt and pepper each of the buttered caps.
Fry bacon and crumble finely.
Chop green onions.
Mince stems of mushrooms.
Mix stems, bacon, bread crumbs and grated cheese together with 1 beaten egg.
Stuff mushroom caps with stem mixture.
Broil for 8 minutes in oven, until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter or margarine.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter or margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently with hand.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Store, loosely covered.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage.
Cover for 5 minutes; add salt.
Cabbage liquid may be used in white sauce.
Place cabbage in dish.
Pour over sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll dough out in 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Beat eggs and cover top of dough with egg.
Cook sausage.
Drain and sprinkle over dough.
Shred pepper cheese and sprinkle over sausage.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese next.
Add parsley flakes (for color).
Roll jelly-roll fashion and crimp all sides.
Smear rest of egg mixture on top.
Put in large heavy pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves bread.
Can be shaped in pan as desired.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Place English muffins on cookie sheet.
Spoon on some spaghetti sauce.
Add cheese and ground beef.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted and bread is toasted.

title: hallie's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter, mix rice and put in casserole dish. Cut up chicken, put on rice and add broccoli.
Soften cheese in microwave, mix with soup.
Add to casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch or 9-inch square baking pan.
Beat butter and sugar 5 to 8 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour to make smooth dough.
Knead dough evenly in bottom of greased pan.
Prick dough with a fork.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown

title: drumsticks and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ovenproof dish, place drumsticks. Combine the soup and 1 soup can water; spoon over drumsticks. Sprinkle basil on top.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally, or until drumsticks are fork-tender and juices run clear when pierced.
Remove drumsticks; keep warm.

title: meat crust pie
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pack into 9-inch pie pan to cover the bottom and sides.
Press another pie pan on top.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 7 minutes.
Remove upper pan.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes more.
Turn vegetables and tomatoes into this hot meat shell.
Garnish with green pepper rings. Return to oven.
Bake 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and place in oven 2 to 3 minutes to melt.
Remove pan and add remaining ingredients in order listed, using back of spoon to flatten each layer.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and refrigerate until cold before cutting.
Yields 36 bars with 142 calories per bar.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter.
Cook onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, pepper, pimento, green pepper and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sticky buns(makes about 12)
directions: Thoroughly grease a Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls inside (you may need to break apart).
Melt margarine or butter and add brown sugar.
Sprinkle pudding mix over rolls.
Combine melted butter and brown sugar and drizzle mixture over rolls.
You may wish to use a knife to get in between rolls so mixture will be between all rolls.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cinnamon. Cover with greased foil and leave overnight to rise.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in a double boiler.
Add mayo and horseradish.
Mix well.
Chill and spread on crackers.

title: banana cake and frosting
directions: Stir shortening, just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add bananas and half the buttermilk. Mix until all flour is dampened, then beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk and eggs. Beat 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in two 9-inch layer pans.

title: custard poi mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake(really moist; rather large)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs (one at a time, unbeaten).
Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Add flour and soda, sifted together.
Alternate with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 350° in 9-inch layer pans (angel cake pan can be used).

title: etta's chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts and debone.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread peas and carrots over chicken.
Mix celery soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick, milk and melted margarine and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt in microwave almond bar and chocolate chips. Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: pelican honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large wooden bowl as listed.
Put in a glass container and refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well; chill overnight.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, Miracle Whip and Ranch dressing. Spread over cooled crescent rolls, then top with 9 vegetables listed and shredded cheese.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with rhubarb; sprinkle evenly with sugar.
Slowly pour half and half over top of rhubarb.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes, or until firm.
Serve warm or chilled with whipped topping if desired.
(Frozen rhubarb can be used, but must be thawed before adding to cake batter.)

title: james' crab & shrimp stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a sauce pan combine 1 cup of the heavy cream; cook until reduced to half.
Stir in shallots and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir 1/2 cup of the coconut milk, cracker crumbs, shrimp, crab meat, salt, pepper, and dill.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Place in shallow casserole dish.
In a sauce pan reduce the remaining 1 cup heavy cream to half.
Stir in the remaining 1/4 cup coconut milk and spinach and cook for 2 min.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour sauce over mushrooms, bake for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until lemon-colored.
Beat in sugar gradually, approximately 5 minutes.
Fold in flour, baking powder and salt. Turn into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until surface springs back when pressed.

title: bagel breakfast
directions: Beat cheese and milk.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread on toasted bagel halves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, shortening, margarine and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: basic pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter until light.
Add sugar to butter gradually until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour and milk to the creamed batter, beginning and ending with the flour gradually.
Blend lemon and vanilla flavorings.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured cake.

title: stir and roll pastry
directions: Stir together flour and salt. Combine oil and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Divide into 2 balls of dough.
Roll dough between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Place in pie pan(s).

title: preacher's cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cream eggs and sugar. Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Add pineapple, vanilla then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: spanish style pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in greased baking dish.
Top with 1 tablespoon rice and 1 onion, slice each.
Pour soup on top.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° until tender.

title: georgiana's stew
directions: Cook in electric skillet at 350° for 2 hours.
Add meat to water with seasonings and cook 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients and finish for 1 hour.
Some cooking times may vary.
Stir occasionally.
You may need to add a little water as needed.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: joanne's southern barbecued pig
directions: In covered pot, boil 6 inches of rib end pork loin cut into 3/4 to 1 inch slices in water, 1/2 up the level of the meat, 2 to 3 hours until it falls apart.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste to the pot during the cooking.
Strain pot liquid, cool and remove fat from the top.
Reserve it for adding as necessary to keep the meat moist.
Pick meat apart into slivers, put into pot with cider vinegar and Tabasco sauce.
Blend flavors over low heat at least 20 minutes adding pot liquor as needed to keep meat moist and from sticking to bottom of pot.
Serve hot on buns or rolls with cole slaw and extra Tabasco.
Makes 8 to 12 sandwiches.

title: ice cream(6-quart)
directions: Separate 6 eggs and beat yolks until thick and yellow.
Take pint of milk and stir in 3 cups of sugar and 2 tablespoons of flour.
Add yolks and cook until thick.

title: apricot balls
directions: Stir together and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pinwheels
directions: Tortillas should be fresh and soft.
In a mixing bowl, add chopped green chilies, olive oil, onion powder and garlic powder. Mix well.
Allow cream cheese to soften and add to green chilie mixture.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over tortilla, then roll and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Chill for an hour before serving.

title: southern baked ham
directions: Parboil ham in large pot for 2 hours.
Remove from pot. Marinate with Coke and pineapple juice.
Place in refrigerator overnight (trim excess fat off).
Bring 3 cups of water to a boiling point.
Add cloves, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over ham.
Decorate with pineapple slices, using toothpicks.
Cook in oven at 300° for 2 hours or until well cooked.

title: irish bannock
directions: Rub margarine into flour and salt.
Add sugar and sultanas. Add beaten egg.
Mix into a soft dough with milk.
Bake in a greased loaf tin for 30 minutes.
Set oven temperature at 475° or gas mark 7.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown pork in large frypan real brown; pour out fat and add flour.
Brown; add all remaining ingredients and simmer at low temperature for 20 minutes.
In bowl, mix corn bread mix as directed.
Spray baking pan with oil; pat a thin coat of the corn bread mix in bottom of pan.
Pour the chili or spoon into pan; top with rest of corn bread mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new pumpkin pie
directions: Combine the marshmallows, cooked pumpkin, salt, cinnamon and ginger in the top of a double boiler.
Heat the mixture over half a pot of boiling water until the marshmallows are melted, stirring as the mixture melts.
Let cool to room temperature.

title: tater tot casserole(marie's)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef with onions and green peppers. Stir in salt and pepper.
Layer in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan as follows:
beef mixture, uncooked peas, diluted chicken soup and Tater Tots.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in the bottom of
a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix,
nuts
and
melted
butter.
(Mixture
will
be crumbly.) Sprinkle
over
pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or
Cool Whip.
Makes
8 to 10 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Combine sugar, flour and spices.
Add mixture to peaches; mix lightly.
Spoon peach mixture into 9-inch pastry.
Use lattice work top crust.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.

title: easy cobbler dough
directions: Melt the margarine in baking dish.
Pour batter over margarine.
Pour drained fruit (your choice) over batter.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham crackers.
Press into pan. Put Eagle Brand milk on cracker crumbs, then semi-sweet chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Put flour in pan like making biscuits.
Use hot water; put in egg, then mix.
Roll out very thin.
Let broth be boiling; put dumplings in.
When finished, stir and take off stove.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake 30 minutes longer. Cover with the noodles and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: apple rolls
directions: Knead well and chill until stiff.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk; stir over medium heat until warm.
Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Gradually add to milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and coconut; remove from heat and pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut and bake until brown.

title: graham pudding
directions: Put all together and steam for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, add onion, green pepper and other seasonings. Add cubed cheese; stir over low heat until cheese melts; add soup and water.
Mix with cooked spaghetti in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Yields 5 to 7 servings.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli using package directions, drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth, cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream and wine.
Place broccoli crosswise in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over.
Top with chicken.
To remaining sauce, add cheese; pour over chicken; sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until heated through.
Then broil just until sauce is golden, about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chipped dried beef white sauce
directions: Brown chipped dried beef in butter.
Mix milk with flour until smooth.
(May shake in container to mix).
Add milk mixture to frypan and stir until it thickens.
May be served over toast or cooked noodles.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: prize coffee cake
directions: Sift together 1st four ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: larry and tiff's punch
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add remaining ingredients. Freeze.
Makes a lot.

title: crunchy broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender using water or stock.
Retain liquid.
Layer broccoli in buttered casserole.
Combine the bread crumbs, wheat germ, sesame seed and seasonings.
Sprinkle this mixture over broccoli.
Cover with chopped cashews.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Stir in tomatoes, okra and basil.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onions into a bowl of water to cover.
When ready to mix all ingredients, drain and rinse potatoes and onions and dry with a tea towel, as dry as possible. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased grill or frypan.
Cook until brown and tender when pierced with a fork. Serve with applesauce and sour cream on the side.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add cocoa, sugar and vanilla.
Cook until bubbly.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add oatmeal.
Take off fire.
Mix in oatmeal and pour on cookie sheet.
Cut when cool and serve.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Mix and press Oreo cookies (crushed) and 3/4 stick melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften vanilla ice cream and spread over Oreo crust.
Put in freezer and let harden.

title: hobo hash
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-low heat.
Combine ham, onion, potatoes and broccoli in skillet, stirring until potatoes are browned.
Reduce heat to low and sprinkle with cheese.
Continue heating until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and divide equally onto two plates.
Top each serving with 1 tablespoon sour cream and serve immediately.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: In large bowl, mix well with fork the flour, sugar and salt. Add shortening and mix with fork until crumbly.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and salt to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows and peanut butter before removing from fire.
Cool. Add vanilla.
Beat until thick after cooling.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cafeteria-style eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1-inch cubes.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine eggplant, onions, celery and margarine.
Cover and microwave on High power 8 to 10 minutes; do not drain.
Add stewed tomatoes, including liquid, stuffing mix, stock, salt and pepper.
Re-cover and microwave on High power 4 minutes.
Top with cheese and microwave on High power 1 minute or until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.
This casserole freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cut carrots first.
Combine sugars, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together (flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda) at low speed for 1 minute.
Add carrots at low speed to dry ingredients.
Grease pan very lightly. Preheat oven
and bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours in greased Bundt pan.
Keep at room temperature.

title: apple cider salad(this is a great fall salad.)
directions: Heat cider to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in cider, then add lemon juice and salt.
Cool until the mixture begins to gel, then add all the other ingredients.
Pour into a large serving bowl and refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions.
Set aside.
Cook rice in the 4 cups of boiling water (per cooking instructions).
After the 5 minute period, add stuffing mix, seasoning, soup, celery, onions, vegetables and mushrooms. Mix.
Place in large casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese slices (you might add cheese after baking for 15 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers; set aside.
Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add wafers, coconut and nuts.

title: peppers and steak
directions: Fry steak and onion in frying pan until brown a little.
Put in green peppers; put in tomato sauce and 1 cup water and cook until done.

title: roast chicken parts and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, combine 1 teaspoon oil, garlic, lemon peel, thyme and 1/2 of the salt and pepper.
Add chicken and onions; toss well to coat evenly.
Place in a 14-inch pan; roast for 40 minutes.
Combine remaining oil, garlic, salt and pepper with vegetables in bowl, getting them well coated.
The last 15 to 20 minutes, add vegetables to the chicken; continue roasting until tender.
(Low-fat.)

title: key lime pie
directions: Add lime rind, lime juice and food coloring to condensed milk; blend until thick and smooth.
Stir in egg yolks; blend well. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool 2 to 3 hours. Keep refrigerated.

title: white bread
directions: Heat water and oil until warm.
Add sugar, salt and yeast. Stir until foamy.
Add flour in 2 cups at a time.
Use all the flour.
Knead on floured towel until smooth, until no air bubbles show.
Pour in a greased bowl.
Let rise.
Punch down and then let rise again.
Shape rolls or bread loaves.
Bake at 375° or until golden brown.
Bread will sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from pan and grease top.
Cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in pot and boil 1 or 1 1/2 minutes or until it forms a ball in cold water; beat with mixer until thick. Pour into pan and cut.

title: baked beans
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, combine beans, brown sugar, mustard and ketchup; mix well.
Fold in chopped onion and green pepper.
Top with sliced bacon.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice the vegetables and steak into thin strips.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Saute vegetables until onion is transparent. Remove from pan and set them aside.
Reheat pan.
Over medium flame, brown steak, stirring often.
Add gravy and vegetables (including any juices that settled).
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover, reduce heat and simmer at least 30 minutes, no more than 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers, remove seeds and membranes.
Put into boiling water and set aside for 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
Cook ground beef in skillet; drain excess fat.
Add 3/4 to 1 can of mushroom soup, undiluted.
Add crushed potato chips.
Mixture should be of a soft consistency.
If too dry, add more soup.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Put shredded lettuce in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle the celery, then the water chestnuts, then the frozen peas (breaking up clumps as necessary), over the lettuce.
Cover with mayonnaise (spread it like frosting).
Mix together and sprinkle on top the sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Spread the grated cheese to cover the top. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before serving, top with bacon, tomatoes and eggs.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer.
Put refried beans on bottom of casserole dish, then add sour cream (spread evenly), then put Cheddar cheese on top. If you wish, you can put chopped green onions on top. Refrigerate.

title: slaw
directions: Grate vegetables; toss together.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over slaw mixture while hot. Refrigerate.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: simple pie
directions: Beat together and pour into crust.
Top with strawberry, cherry, or blueberry pie filling.
As an added treat, line the bottom of the graham cracker crust with kiwi fruit and/or bananas.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Meanwhile remove shrimp scales and remove veins.
Drop
in
boiling water for 3 minutes and drain. Strain juice from crushed pineapple.
Peel and core apples, cut into small pieces.
Dice
onion
and
celery.
After shrimp has cooled, mix
all ingredients together.
Drain remaining juices. Mix in
walnuts.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise before serving.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and eggs; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add butter and nuts; pour into pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Cook rice as directed; saute onion, celery and bell pepper. Brown sausage.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: lucy's carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool and remove from pan.
Frost with pineapple frosting.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Steam all vegetables in a steamer until tender.
Saute mushrooms in a little water or oil in skillet.
Now, add all ingredients together.
Toss and serve.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mash tomatoes in a saucepan (I use a potato masher).
Add to the tomatoes the ground beef and the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer at least 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
This makes a pretty table to freeze in individual servings and place on table before serving meal, especially in crystal sherbets.

title: sweetened broccoli salad
directions: Combine dressing ingredients, then toss with salad ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and peaches.
Mix all ingredients together with the fruit cocktail and peaches and stir very well. Put in the refrigerator until you serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook red potatoes.
After cooked, quarter unpeeled.
While warm, add fresh parsley, olive oil, garlic flavored vinegar, garlic powder and pepper to taste.
Mix.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour with baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour in greased, floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 300°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.

title: peach delight salad
directions: To peach Jell-O, add 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup of the peach juice.
Add the pint of ice cream to hot mixture.
Let melt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add peaches, coconut and pecans.
Put peaches on top if you want.
Best to let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Then add eggs (beaten well), bananas and nuts all at once.
Mix thoroughly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, if preferred.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°; then lower heat to 350°. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: apple ginger bread
directions: Mix cereal, molasses, shortening and water.
Add egg and beat with beater.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour, soda, powder and spices and salt.
Add cereal mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Arrange apples in layers over top.
Brush with mixture of butter and syrup.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush apples with milk and broil just a few minutes.

title: blueberry delight pie
directions: Place chopped nuts in bottom of pie shell and bake.
Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Add Dream Whip with almond and vanilla. Fold Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture together.
Place mixture in pie shell and refrigerate.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with persimmon pulp.
Add raisins and nuts; beat throughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by spoonful (size optional), about 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Spread pie mix in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer pineapple on top; cover evenly with cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Melt oleo and pour over the top.
Bake in oven at 350° until top is browned.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine, then mix eggs and sugar.
Then add nuts and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Beat well oleo, Crisco and sugar until light, about 5 minutes. Add flour and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat at high speed.
Beat until soft and fluffy.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: nutjammer cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll 1/16-inch; cut into 2-inch squares.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell peppers in oleo.
Add cheese and milk. Pour over potatoes and ham.
Bake at 325° until heated.
Serve.

title: light and luscious fish fry
directions: Rinse the fish and pat dry.
Cut into 16 equal pieces.
In a cup, combine the mustard, yogurt, chives, parsley and pepper.
Rub this mixture onto all sides of the fish.
Refrigerate for about 20 minutes.
Coat the fish pieces with bread crumbs.
Coat a baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Add the fish in a single layer, with space between the pieces.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until the fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Set aside.

title: red rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine and olive oil until soft in a medium-size saucepan.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, broth, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender or liquid is absorbed.
Fluff up rice and serve!
Makes about 8 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Boil the water	and
1	cup
sugar together.
Add cornstarch moistened with a little water and cook 5 minutes.
Then put in the yolks
of
the
eggs,
lemon juice, grated rind and salt.
Cool slightly and pour into the baked pie crust.
Cover with the meringue made
by beating the whites of the eggs with 2 tablespoons sugar.	Put into moderately hot (375°) oven and brown the meringue.

title: after school soup
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse. Bring to a boil tomato juice and soda, stir until foamy.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and oleo.
Add macaroni and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: easy pecan pralines
directions: Mix the ingredients except pecans in a heavy saucepan and cook and stir over low heat until the sugar dissolves.
Add pecans; cook and stir until a full over boil; reduce heat and cook slowly 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often, until candy reaches soft ball stage (test in cool water).
Take off heat until thick, but shiny. Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Makes about 24 patties.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Stir together the dry ingredients.
Mix together the liquid ingredients; add to dry mixture, mixing until smooth.
Pour into greased pans (9 x 13-inches or two 9-inch round).
Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes for layers or approximately 40 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and crumbs. Heat to blend. Grease 2 casserole dishes. Line with layer of crumbs, chicken and soup mixture. Continue to layer and finish with crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 50 minutes.

title: tomatoes carni
directions: Cut a slice from the top of each tomato and hollow out the insides using a teaspoon or grapefruit knife.
Leave only the meaty part which adhered to the skin.
Salt the insides; sprinkle with a pinch of sugar.
Turn upside down and drain for 30 minutes. Pat dry with paper towels.
Arrange in a shallow buttered baking dish.
Put small pat of butter in each tomato.
Bake in preheated 400° oven, occasionally brushing the outsides with some of the butter from the interiors, for 10 minutes.
Take care not to overcook or the tomatoes will lose their shape.
Fill with buttered fresh peas.

title: cheese dip
directions: Blend well with the mixer.
Serve with crisp crackers or chips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add parsley, gravy and tomatoes, then meat.
Bring to boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour, until liquid is greatly reduced.
Put mixture in shallow baking dish.
Heap with mashed potatoes.
Brown under a hot broiler.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate dried beef in blender until fine. Mix cream cheese, onions and Accent with handful of dried beef together until well blended. Form 1 large ball. Dip ball in the rest of the dried beef.

title: bay state buffalo pot roast
directions: In a large pot, cook cranberries with sugar in 3/4 cup water for 10 minutes.
Place buffalo roast into pot.
Add hot water, bouillon cubes, horseradish, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Stir. Cover pot and bring to boil.
Lower heat, tilt cover and keep meat 3/4 covered with liquid.
Add water and bouillon, if necessary. Turn meat occasionally.
Cook gently for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from pot and slice.
Return slices (1/2 to 1-inch thick) to pot. Continue cooking gently for 1/2 hour.
Add onions and carrots. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook gently 1/2 hour or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, powdered sugar, granulated sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Chill dough for easier handling (overnight).
roll dough by teaspoonful, making a ball and roll in sugar.
Press down on slightly greased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until little brown.

title: crab-swiss crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Prior to serving, place 1 teaspoon of mixture on a Ritz cracker and heat in microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: cinnamon streusel cake
directions: Blend all the ingredients at medium speed 2 minutes. Do not overmix.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix the last 3 ingredients with chicken seasoning.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Toss.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix well and bake in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut and some nuts on top.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: praline cookies
directions: Break crackers into bar size pieces.
Place with edges touching on greased foil in pan.
Bring butter and sugar to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Add nuts. Pour evenly over crackers and bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from foil and separate.
May be stored in airtight container or frozen.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Sift flour; add sugar, soda and salt in bowl.
Combine egg, vanilla and flour (undrained).
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Pour in 6 x 10-inch dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ranger joe cookies
directions: Beat well shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool and break apart.
Set aside.
Drain pineapple and add sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip last. Add to the broken pieces when ready to use.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat pear juice and pour over jello.
Mash drained pears with a fork.
Soften pears with a little juice.
Add mashed pears to cheese and pour into jello.
Let cool.
Fold Cool Whip into jello mixture and pour into mold or pan.
Chill, then cut into squares or slice when set.

title: huevas (egg) rancheros
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Combine hot peppers, garlic and tomatoes.
Mash and add to the pan with onion. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Scramble or prepare easy over eggs.
Pour the tomato mixture over top of eggs and garnish with bacon strips, fresh parsley, orange or tomato slices.

title: butterfinger frosting
directions: Mix caramel ice cream topping and Eagle Brand milk; pour over cooked cake (punch holes in top of cake so it will run down into the cake).	Crumble Butterfinger candy bars on top of mixture; top with Cool Whip.
Crumble more Butterfinger candy bars on top of Cool Whip.	Refrigerate.

title: creek bank coffee
directions: Remove insides from coffeepot and throw away.
Pour coffee in water and boil for 5 minutes.
Grounds will sink; pour easy.

title: vegetable rice ring
directions: Combine cooked rice and Italian dressing.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add mayo to undrained rice mixture and stir until combined. Fold in radishes, cucumbers, tomatoes, green pepper, celery and green onion. Press into a 5 1/2- cup ring mold.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Melt butter; add sugar and curry powder.
Put fruit in casserole.
Cover with butter mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Check in 15 to 20 minutes.
Add almonds or other nuts, if desired.

title: no fuss chicken
directions: Pour Egg Beaters into shallow bowl large enough to dip chicken.
Roll chicken in flour.
Fry in a frying pan with 1/4 cup oil until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: apple kucken coffee cake
directions: Cut softened butter in dry cake mix.
Stir until crumbly. Stir in coconut.
Pat lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Build up slightly at edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm cake.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Drizzle on apples.
Bake for 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and sliced peaches in a separate bowl. Put cherries, kiwi, bananas, peaches and fruit cocktail in another bowl.
In the bowl with the juice drained from the fruit cocktail and peaches, empty 1 box vanilla pudding.
Stir until well mixed and pour over fruit.
Mix well.

title: chili con caso
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add tomatoes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Melt in cheese.
Add peppers to taste.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: chicken egg rolls
directions: Filling:
In skillet, cook cabbage, celery and onions in oil until just tender.
Add chicken, bean sprouts, carrot, soy sauce and egg.
Mix with hands.
Place 1/4 cup filling in center of egg roll wrapper.
Roll up, folding in sides to enclose filling.
Seam edge with egg.
Fry egg rolls, a few at a time, in 375° oil until lightly brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm with soy sauce or other sweet and sour sauces.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine sugar and peanut butter.
Mix to crumbly consistency, remove half of mixture; set aside.
Spread remaining mixture evenly over pie crust.
Make pudding following directions.
Pour over crumb layer.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, cover with whipped topping and top with reserved peanut butter mix.

title: no peek skillet chicken
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms and garlic clove.
Combine with onion soup mix.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sausage strata(fix the night before; bake in morning)
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, beginning with bread cubes.
Cover with sausage and pour egg mixture over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Great brunch with Caramel Rolls.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, cream of tartar and oleo.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda.
Popped corn should be in large roaster pan.
Pur syrup over corn.
Stir until well coated.
Put in preheated 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: slop
directions: Fry first 6 ingredients until potatoes are done.
Beat approximately 6 eggs.
Put cheese on top of potato mixture.
Pour eggs over top.
When eggs settle, stir around until cheese is melted and eggs are done.

title: david's sausage casserole
directions: Lightly brown Rice-A-Roni in butter.
Add 2 3/4 cups hot water.
Stir in beef flavor packet.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add browned sausage links which have been cut into 1-inch pieces.
Put in casserole.
Pour tomato sauce over and sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter together.
Add the nuts and Cool Whip.
Fold into the baked crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: burritos
directions: Brown and drain meats.
Add taco seasoning and picante sauce. Soften tortillas (S at A time) in microwave for 45 seconds.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons of meat and 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese on side of tortilla nearest you.
Roll approximately 2/3 the width of the tortilla.
Fold the ends in and roll the rest of the way.
Fry, flap side down, in enough oil to cover burrito halfway until golden brown.
Turn and fry the other side until golden brown.
Yields 20 burritos.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add to sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, then other ingredients.
Pour in 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cornmeal batter fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken, if desired.
Rinse chicken.
In a large saucepan, cover chicken with lightly salted water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Pat chicken pieces dry with paper towels.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Use a double pie crust to fit a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, rosemary or poultry seasoning and pepper.
Add broth; stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cubed chicken, vegetables and pimento; heat until bubbly.
Pour mixture into pan on top of bottom crust.
Cover with top crust; cut holes for steam release.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy; add sugar and knead. Shape into eggs.
Dip into Chocolate Coating.

title: antipasto
directions: Arrange on plate.
Drizzle with olive oil just before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: heaven
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/4 cup; bring to boil.
Dissolve with jello and put in ice cube tray and chill until slightly firm.
Have milk very cold and whip until stiff.
Add jello and beat well.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallows.
Let sit until firm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together Karo, peanuts, sugar and salt in ovenproof dish. Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir.
Microwave 4 minutes more.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Add baking soda. Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto sheet of foil.
Let cool 1 hour.
Break into small pieces when cool.

title: venison steak
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together and dip steak slices.
Cover both sides, then roll into flour and fry until a golden brown. this is good to fry to nearly done and simmer in the milk gravy recipe below.

title: bread pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl tear up bread.
Pour 1 quart of cream over bread and set aside.
Break up eggs and add sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add salt and vanilla. Continue to beat while adding remaining 1/2 quart of coffee creamer.
After mixing thoroughly, pour into pan with melted butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Place into a larger pan with 1/4 inch water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a knife comes out clean.

title: butterscotch oatmeal crispies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and oats.
In small bowl, mix shortening, vanilla, salt, soda and hot water.
Beat into sugar mixture.
Chill.
Roll dough in 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to rack to cool.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: herbed butter spread
directions: Mix and let set at least 45 minutes. Spread on bread and broil.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Put ice cream salt on bottom of roaster.
Cover salt with water.
Put the roast, seasoned with salt and pepper and rubbed with Worcestershire sauce all over, in on top of salt.
Cover with ice cream salt until roast disappears.
Sprinkle with water.
Set oven at 500°.
Roast for 15 minutes per pound.

title: ohio buckeye candy
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Form into balls. Stick toothpicks into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate until nearly covered, leaving some peanut butter mixture exposed on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and margarine (I use all butter).
Add rest of ingredients, beating after each addition. Stir in nuts.
Drop by half teaspoon on cookie sheet sprayed with Baker's Secret or lined with tin foil.
Bake 15 minutes or less at 350° until edges are brown.

title: clam cheese pie
directions: Melt butter; mix all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into pie plate. Cut 1/4 strips of cheese and lay on top in crisscross pattern. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers, toast points or chips.

title: chicken t
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and cover bottom of greased large casserole.
Add chicken.
Mix soups, mayonnaise, egg and lemon juice; spread over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Melt butter and add to dressing.
(I also add some chicken broth.)
Spoon over soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil approximately 5 pounds unpeeled Idaho potatoes in salted water until they pierce easily with a fork, being careful not to overcook.
Remove from water; peel and dice potatoes.
Place in a large ceramic or glass bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients with potatoes thoroughly.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
This potato salad will keep very well refrigerated.
Improved with age.

title: easy punch
directions: Empty ingredients into a gallon jar.
Fill the remainder with water and mix well.

title: cocktail meatballs(yields approximately 120)
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, eggs, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper gently.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Beat well.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in shredded zucchini.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bread sticks
directions: For hot sticks, mix butter with taco mix.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (or cookie sheet with one inch or more sides).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In 2 1/2-quart crock-pot, mix all ingredients.
Let simmer on high for 2 hours.
Serve.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Marinate broccoli, tomatoes and olives for 3 hours in dressing.
Combine with noodles and cheese.
Toss lightly and eat.

title: grandma rheba's ginger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed in order, gradually until dough is thick.
Roll onto floured surface and add flour until dough is stiff.
Roll out and cut into shapes of your choice.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes.
Let cool, enjoy!

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook onions in drippings until tender; add bacon to pork and beans in tomato sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: eggplant or squash casserole
directions: Cook eggplant with onion until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix cheese and crumbs; set aside.
Mix eggplant, egg, 1/2 milk, salt, pepper, butter and 1/2 of cheese and cracker mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Add remaining crumbs and bake at 350° until set and browned.

title: oven french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, melted butter, corn syrup, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and spread evenly to cover bottom of pan.
Slice bread 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick and place over syrup mixture.
Beat milk, eggs and vanilla together and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes in 325° oven.
Use spatula to remove each slice from pan and turn syrup side up on plates.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine pineapple with juice, eggs, sugar and flour. Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Cut bread into squares.
Melt butter in pan.
When hot, add bread and brown.
Put on top of pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Pour strawberry Jell-O mix and water into glass dish (sprayed with Pam).
Dissolve, then pour crushed pineapple and frozen strawberries into Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: corn flakes snack
directions: Melt sugar and syrup.
Take off stove and stir in peanut butter.
Mix in corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Cook sausage, crumbling with a fork, until no longer pink. Drain and cool.
Add cheese, Bisquick and water.
Mix with fork just until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on a large cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until well puffed and browned.
Makes about 50.

title: swiss steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour, salt and pepper; brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Mushrooms may be added.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onions until tender and drain.
Then mash, leaving some lumps.
Add all other ingredients as desired.
Could also add Bordeaux seasoning to make soup spicy.
Could also add grated or bits of cheese as desired.
Carrots, broccoli, cauliflower or squash could be substituted for potatoes.

title: oatmeal krispies
directions: Prepare the original Rice Krispies Treats recipe.
Press mixture into a 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan coated with cooking spray.
Cool completely, about 30 minutes.
Cut down the center into 2 halves.
Spread 1 cup prepared chocolate frosting on one half and place second half on top, to form 2 layers.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Gently cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Yields 15 sandwiches.

title: orange spiced carrots
directions: Wash carrots and pare them with a vegetable peeler.
Remove ends.
Cut carrots crosswise into 1/4-inch rounds.
In a saucepan, put water, orange juice and margarine.
Add carrots.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat 25 minutes or until carrots are crisp and tender.
Check to make sure that carrots do not burn, because most of the liquid will be absorbed.
Add a few tablespoons of water if necessary.
Sprinkle carrots with vanilla and orange rind; mix well.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth into soup in 2-quart casserole.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican macaroni casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage, onions and green peppers. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes, sour cream, chili powder, sugar and salt.
Add uncooked macaroni.
