Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring frequently to avoid sticking until tender.

title: red delicious fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit; toss with Yogurt Dressing.
Arrange in lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish with apple slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach-blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugars, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Spread blueberries in pastry-lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar-flour mixture and half of lemon juice.

title: waldorf salad deluxe
directions: Into a large bowl, squeeze juice from lemon.
Stir in mayonnaise, celery salt, white pepper and cardamom.
Cut unpeeled apples and pears into 1-inch chunks.
Cut each grape in half.
Stir apples, pears, grapes and celery into mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: the reuben revised
directions: Spread bread slices with dressing.
Layer 1 slice of bread with sauerkraut, turkey pastrami and cheese.
Top with remaining bread slice.
Melt margarine in small, nonstick skillet on medium heat. Place sandwich in skillet and cover.
Heat 3 minutes on each side or until sandwich is lightly browned and cheese is slightly melted. Makes 1 sandwich.
Calories:
Traditional Reuben Calories: 970.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain juice off vegetables.
Then mix all ingredients and bake for 20 minutes.

title: world war i cake
directions: Mix and boil for 5 minutes the brown sugar, hot water, shortening, raisins, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Cool, then add flour, baking soda and hot water. Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle dates with 3/4 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour boiling water over dates, let stand until cool.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, leaving out butter. Set aside to cool.
In large bowl, combine chicken, broth, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add red pepper, celery, onions and reserved rice.
Gently stir in green peas and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Serves 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Add milk and corn; mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gramma's moist carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon twice. Combine sugar and oil. Beat well. Then blend in carrots and drained pineapple. Beat eggs, one at a time. Add to carrot mixture, then add to the dry ingredients. Pour in ungreased pan (Bundt pan works well also). Bake 1 hour or slightly longer until done.

title: apricot-pecan pastry
directions: Combine pie crust mix, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add about 5 tablespoons water until mixture is moistened and forms a ball. Divide dough into 24 one inch balls.
Press each ball into 1 3/4-inch muffin cups to cover bottoms and sides of tin.
Combine pie filling, milk and lemon peel.
Spoon a rounded teaspoon of filling into each cup.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° approximately 15 minutes or just until pastries begin to brown. Yield: 24 pastries.

title: ranch salad
directions: Prepare lettuce, tomatoes and onion as you would for tossed salad.
Add beans.
Chill.
Just before serving, add the cheese, Fritos and meat (if used).
Toss well.
Add Catalina dressing and stir to completely coat salad.

title: refrigerator pie pastry
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
Add salt, milk and vinegar and beaten egg.
Blend altogether.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 6 crusts.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk, and butter together and pour into a greased 9x13 inch casserole.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: For crust:
Boil
margarine
and
water.
Add flour and beat until it forms a ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Grease a
9 x 13-inch pan and spread the mixture in it. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ohio-swedish nut cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: million dollar spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute beef and butter until brown and add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Combine cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese, scallions and peppers.
Spread 1/2 spaghetti in a casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Then add rest of spaghetti.
Pour beef mixture over top.
Chill 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt 2 times.
Melt oleo.
Add water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients; mix well. Add eggs, buttermilk (in which soda has been dissolved), and vanilla.
Bake in a greased cake pan at 350° for 20 minutes or until done done in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Put grated potatoes in bowl; add eggs, onion and flour mixture, beating thoroughly with spoon.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
When oil is hot, spoon about 2 tablespoons of batter for each pancake into oil, leaving about 1/2-inch between pancakes.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown and crisp on one side.
Turn carefully and brown on other side.

title: mexican chicken casserole(gloria earnshaw)
directions: Mix together soups and salsa.
Grease 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Line bottom with tortillas (cut in quarters).
Layer chicken, green onions, cheese and soup mixture.
Continue and make last layer cheese (on top).
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: herbed popcorn
directions: Keep popped corn warm.
Cream together margarine, cheese and seasonings.
Pour off any water that is worked out of margarine. Toss cheese mixture with popped corn.
Contains about 75 calories per cup.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix thoroughly the flour, butter and confectioners sugar. Press evenly in bottom of ungreased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Mix in bowl and refrigerate.

title: scallopini burgers
directions: Combine meat and crumbs, egg and milk.
Shape into six patties.
Coat lightly with 1/4 cup flour.
Brown in hot oil. Drain.
Combine tomato sauce, undrained mushrooms, wine, parsley and oregano.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes. Serve over hot noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add grits and salt. Cook slowly for 10 to 15 minutes or until done. Add garlic, green chilies, cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and garnish with scallions (optional).
Makes 10 servings.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: melba rounds
directions: Note: Optional toppings can be sliced olives or sliced mushrooms.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring until batter is moistened.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press 1 large crescent roll on bottom, up to 1 inch on sides.
Beat 1 cup sugar, 1 egg yolk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and the 2 packages cream cheese, together.
Cut a piece of wax paper the size of pan and spray it with Pam.
Press the other package of crescent rolls on wax paper and flip it onto cream cheese mixture in pan.
Pinch the dough together.
Beat egg whites with fork and spread on top of crust.
Take 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press kisses into center while hot.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Leave in refrigerator overnight so the flavors will blend together.
Cut raw vegetables to dip size.
I use celery, carrots, mushrooms, cucumber, zucchini, cauliflower and broccoli.

title: best apple cobbler
directions: Combine the biscuit mix, sugar, cream and orange juice in a mixing bowl and stir until dough leaves side of bowl. Knead several times on lightly floured board. Roll out about 3/4 of the dough on a lightly floured board to a 9 x 13-inch rectangle, 1/4-inch thick. Place in baking dish. Slice the apples into thin wedges and arrange over the dough. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and additional sugar. Drizzle the caramel sauce over the cobbler. Roll out the remaining dough and cut into thin strips. Arrange in crisscross fashion over the apples. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned and apples are tender.

title: macaroni lasagna
directions: Heat 1 teaspoon garlic powder, onion, beef, salt and pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes and hot water.
Simmer 5 minutes or longer. Blend beaten eggs with cottage cheese in bowl.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Grease a muffin tin. Mix the 3 ingredients. Put into about 10 muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend cheese, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped topping.
Fold in rest of ingredients. Pour into wax paper lined pan (9 x 13-inch).
Freeze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Use 4-quart saucepan.
Bring water, cornstarch and sugar to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Add Jell-O; let cool, then put in sliced strawberries.
Pour into prebaked pie shells. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.
"I have used graham cracker shells."

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bar over hot water.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with chocolate kisses, if desired.
Cool in fridge approximately 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: peanutty drop cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter, peanut butter and shortening with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add about half of the flour, the sugar, brown sugar, eggs, baking soda and vanilla to the margarine mixture.
Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Beat or stir in the remaining flour.
Stir in chopped peanuts.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well.
This is great on baked potatoes, cole slaw or potato salad.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery, onion and salt.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and place in large casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally and add more water, if needed.
Serve over chow mein noodles with soy sauce.

title: halibut with garden style marinara sauce
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Place steaks in a 2-quart square microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with microwave-safe plastic wrap; turn back one corner to vent.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 4 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily, turning and sprinkling with 1/4 teaspoon of the lemon-pepper seasoning.
Let stand while preparing sauce.

title: chicken bacon nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
In bowl, combine chicken, marmalade, soy sauce, salt, ginger and garlic powder.
Cover and let marinate for several hours or overnight in refrigerator. Partially cook bacon.
Cut each slice in half and wrap around each piece of chicken.
Secure with toothpick.
Place bacon wrapped chicken on rack in broiling pan and broil 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, turning nuggets once and brushing with marmalade mixture.
Great appetizer!

title: chicken, broccoli and ziti
directions: Trim broccoli into florets.
Peel stalks and slice a quarter inch thick.
Steam just until crisp, about five minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water to stop cooking.
Saute chicken in olive oil, soy sauce and minced garlic over medium heat, being careful not to burn garlic.
Melt butter in a large pot.
Add the cooked broccoli, the chicken mixture and the cooked ziti.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat, stirring often.
Mix in cheese and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 portions.
Best when made a day ahead and reheated.

title: orsingers scotch cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs, vanilla and syrup.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Roll and cut with round cutter.
Put on cookie sheet and brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 325° until done to touch.

title: sweeney stir-fry
directions: Saute oil and spaghetti until light brown.
Add broth, bouillon and chicken and cook 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook 15 minutes.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Set aside.
Combine onion and butter and celery in pan.
Cook until tender.
Add milk and cubed cream cheese and salt.
Cook until smooth.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until done and brown (1 hour).
Makes 2-quart casserole.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread evenly over cake batter to within 1-inch of edge.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Remove, core and seed tomatoes.
Put through coarse food grinder and drain off all juice. Add water and all other ingredients, except spices. Cook 45 minutes and stir often.
Add spices last 5 minutes.
Pack in jars. Process 10 minutes.

title: pork and macaroni bake
directions: Cook pork, onion and garlic in oil until onion is golden.
Add tomato sauce and paste, mushrooms and seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Alternate layers of macaroni, cheese and meat in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: italian-style meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix very well, even kneading with hands if so needed.
Place mixture in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Let cool for around 30 minutes before slicing.
Delicious!

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine chocolate chips, milk and butter.
Heat over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts.
Fold in chocolate. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan (lined with waxed paper).
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Make 8 dozen.

title: mother's good potatoes
directions: Potatoes should be slightly thawed and placed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine and heat butter, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Soup Mixture:
Mix last 5 ingredients well.

title: old fashioned cinnamon pudding
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1/2 stick butter, 1 1/2 cups water and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar, 1 cup sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and milk.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs (one at a time).
Add dry ingredients a little at a time until all is well blended.
Add carrots, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350°.
Baking time:
2 (9-inch) layers, 30 to 35 minutes; 9 x 13-inch pan, 55 to 60 minutes and tube pan, 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: t l h's cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into 1/2-inch rolls.
Chill well.
Slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Make the jello and allow to congeal.
After set, cut it into 1/2-inch squares.
Whip the cream until in peaks.
Add the sugar and vanilla.
Open pineapple and drain.
Combine all ingredients: jello, whipped cream, pineapple and marshmallows into large serving bowl.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until al dente.
Rinse and drain.
Cut up your choice of raw vegetables.
Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour over pasta and vegetables.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes until soft (about 10 minutes).
Cook sausage and remove from skillet.
Saute onions in sausage grease; add basil and oregano when onions are almost done.
Drain water from potatoes, reserving 1 cup.
Put potatoes and 1 cup potato liquid into soup pot.
Add sausage, onions, milk and corn to pot.
Cook until hot; do not boil.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together beef,
egg and bread crumbs and form small balls. Brown in frying pan and set aside.
Discard grease and in pan, dissolve
grape
jelly,
catsup
and brown sugar.
Add meatballs and simmer 15 minutes.
Can be frozen for future use or refrigerate for
2 days before using.
Makes 100 meatballs. Serve hot.

title: apple-raisin shake
directions: In a blender container, combine milk and raisins.
Cover; blend until nearly smooth.
Add ice cream and applesauce.
Cover and blend until combined.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses. Garnish with apple slices, if desired.
Makes 3 (8-ounce) servings.

title: pork chops with stuffing
directions: Brown pork chops; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside. Make stuffing according to package directions.
Arrange pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in a pork chop, standing, with fat side up; then put in big spoon of stuffing, then slice of onion.
Line up pork chops, stuffing, onion in rows in this order.
Mix soup with 1 can water.
Pour soup over pork chops and dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° at least 1 hour; take cover off and bake 15 minutes more.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil, pumpkin and yogurt in a large bowl on medium speed 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt on low speed 30 seconds. Stir in raisins or nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: harvest apple cake
directions: Pour alternately into a tube pan, starting with batter and ending with apple mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco
and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavorings. Place in tube pan.
Place into cold oven.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Spread 1 cup sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Mix remaining sauce, spinach, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, onion, parsley, mushrooms and oregano. Stuff shells with mixture and place upside down in sauce. Sprinkle top of stuffed shells with Parmesan cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grandma's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sour cream, fold in cool whip.
Layer wafers then bananas in bottom of dish.
Pour the sour cream and cool whip mixture on the top of the bananas, put in refrigerator and chill.

title: tortilla pizza
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over high heat, cook ground beef and onions until brown, stirring frequently.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes to blend flavors.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients until smooth. Beat by hand or mixer.
Add the remaining ingredients to the heated mixture. Chill and serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.
Recipe can be halved (it makes a lot).

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and jalapeno in margarine. Add mushroom soup. Add cream cheese and let melt. Add shrimp. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve warm or cold with crackers.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place frozen broccoli spears in buttered casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise together and pour over broccoli spears.
Spread grated cheese over the top.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle over the top of all.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar, wine, lemon and cinnamon in small pan.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add cranberries and continue cooking, 5 minutes for whole berry sauce or 12 minutes for jelly.
May be strained while hot.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix eggs, shortening and sugars.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in egg mixture.
Add oats, vanilla and chocolate bits.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil over medium heat. Add chicken and brown.
Mix soup, water and vegetable combination well.
Pour this mixture over chicken.
Heat to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: widow finney's country bake
directions: Arrange bread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Layer cooked sausage (fried) or ham and mushrooms over bread.
Add layer of cheeses.
Combine eggs and seasonings, mixing thoroughly.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve the gelatine in soup.
Add mayo.
Chop fine the veggies and add the rest of the ingredients to the soup mixture. Refrigerate for 1 to 4 hours.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Combine
all ingredients and heat for 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cut up chicken.
Put in pot with 3 quarts water, onion, 1 tablespoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and stew until tender. Remove chicken.
Cut meat into one-inch pieces and return to broth.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon, green pepper and onion until clear or limp.
Stir occasionally.
Add corn and when it boils, stir in 1 slightly beaten egg.
Add pepper and salt.
Pour into baking dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and cinnamon.
Cream butter with cream cheese thoroughly.
Beat in sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients well.
Press out with cookie press onto cookie sheet. Decorate, if desired, with colored sugars before baking.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are brown.
This cookie is very light in color when done.
Top should not be brown.

title: milwaukee potato salad
directions: Cook washed, unpared potatoes in salt water until tender. Drain.
Let cool to "handling" temperature.
Mix next 5 ingredients with a fork and set aside.
Peel potatoes; chop into a large bowl. While potatoes are still hot, add eggs, onion (if desired) and parsley flakes.
Toss lightly.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mash bananas,
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Combine butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla and beat.
Add bananas, sour cream and flour mixture.
Beat until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils.
Turn the heat down to low, and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips and remaining ingredients.
Mix well, until smooth.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch pan and cool for 1 to 2 hours. Keep refrigerated.

title: ben's amaretto
directions: Place sugar, water and lemon rind in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove lemon rind and discard.
Add vanilla and chocolate extracts, brandy, almond extract and vodka.
Stir well.
Cool and place in a bottle.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, melted oleo, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
In unbaked pie shell, spread pecans on bottom.
Pour mixture over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until firm.

title: rich chocolate frosting
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate and butter or margarine until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 15 minutes to cool chocolate mixture slightly.

title: broccoli and bean sprouts
directions: Saute the broccoli in the oil.
Add stems first, sliced thin, then add tops, chopped.
Add the bean sprouts and soy sauce. Cover; steam for 10 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, Karo syrup and flavorings.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Turn off, add soda.
Pour over popcorn and stir until all covered.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; mash until smooth (no milk).
Add remaining ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Cool.
May be used anytime within a week.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pina colada smoothie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender until frothy. Yields 6 (1/2 cup each) servings; 42 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: homemade enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat.
Mix enchilada sauce, mushroom soup and chicken soup, then mix all together.
Roll the mixture in the tortillas, then put some of mixture on the tortillas.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: heavenly guava - jello
directions: Put Jell-O in bowl large enough to hold the four cups of liquids.
Stir until Jell-O is completely dissolved, then add the guava juice and the cold water.
Stir.
Pour into Jell-O mold or glass container.
Add fruit and mix well.
Chill until set.
Very nice cut in squares on lettuce leaves with topping.
(I use sugar-free Jell-O.)

title: full meal deal
directions: Cut round steak into small pieces and brown in margarine; season.
In a bowl, mix together cream of mushroom soup and milk and pour mixture onto meat.
Cook until it comes to a boil or thickens.
Remove and let set 10 minutes.
Serve with salad and a bread.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Dissolve soda in sour milk and add alternately with the flour.
Add melted chocolate to batter last. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes three 9-inch layers.

title: banana salad
directions: In small saucepan on low heat, combine egg, sugar and lemon juice.
Stir constantly until sauce bubbles and begins to thicken. Set aside.
Slice bananas lengthwise about 3 inches long, 1/4-inch thick.
Whip cream until it peaks.
Fold in with sauce and pour over bananas.
Sprinkle peanuts on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Pour taco seasoning mix over and cook until done.
Put in a large pan and add beans, hominy, tomato sauce and diced tomatoes and green chilies.
Cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put Tostitos in bowl.
Pour soup over them.
Top with sour cream and hot sauce of your choice.

title: horseradish ham spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve on crackers or rye bread.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moist. Do not beat. Add vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas. Mix in thoroughly with spoon. Divide batter into 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cover cake between layers and all over with following frosting.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Place in cold water until ready to use.

title: linguine with clam sauce for four
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch skillet until sizzling.
Add garlic. Cook over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add parsley, clams and Worcestershire sauce.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, 1 minute more.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in sour cream and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in peppers. Cook and drain linguine.
Serve sauce over linguine with Parmesan cheese and pepper.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Combine oil, beaten egg, milk and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Stir together all remaining dry ingredients and stir into liquid ingredients until well blended.
Do not beat. Fill tins 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spiral shaped noodles for 7 to 10 minutes.
Rinse in cool water.
Shake in some Viva Italian to noodles to separate.
Add any or all of the above ingredients to your salad, then shake in as much dressing to coat vegetables evenly.
Chill before serving.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all in blender.
Fill blender with ice cubes to between 4 and 5-cup mark.
Blend.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place on a rack in the pan so fat will run off.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Fifteen minutes before done, top with mixture of catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna (short cut style)
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat.
Add next 4 ingredients. Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut up cooked chicken (deboned) and place in oblong pan. Combine chicken soup and broth.
Bring to a boil and pour over chicken.
Slice eggs on top of that.
Combine buttermilk, oleo and flour.
Stir well and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 or 35 minutes or until brown.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and mix the beans. Mix the last 4 ingredients to make the dressing. Pour the dressing over the beans and mix well. Let set in the refrigerator for several hours.

title: banana split delight
directions: Mix melted margarine with cracker crumbs.
Press mixture in bottom of sheet cake pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Chill.
Add cornstarch to juice; return to pineapple.
Cream together the powdered sugar, margarine and eggs.
Beat for 10 minutes (very important).
Add vanilla.
Place this mixture on chilled crumbs.
Then add bananas, then add pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip evenly over top.
Chill well before serving with maraschino cherries.
Nuts and coconut may be sprinkled on top.

title: zuppa inglese
directions: Butter a loaf pan.
Slice pound cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 layer in pan.
Sprinkle with rum.
Spread cake with jam.
Add a layer of pudding, another layer of cake, sprinkle with rum and spread jam.
Add pudding.
Add last layer of cake; sprinkle with lots of rum.
Refrigerate.
Make up to 3 days in advance to let flavor meld.
Turn pan upside down and remove cake. Cover with Cool Whip and chocolate shavings.
Chill well before serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve. When ready to serve, add a chilled 2 liter bottle of 7-Up.

title: hershey's syrup brownies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour and baking soda, alternating with syrup.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 inch square pan at 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Frost and cut into squares while warm.
Make frosting by heating together the margarine, syrup, vanilla and confectioners sugar, stirring until smooth.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls into their individual triangles, then cover each triangle with the deviled ham spread.
Drain asparagus spear juice into bowl and save.
Place 1 to 3 asparagus spears on the wide end of each triangle, then roll toward the tip.
Cut remaining spears into 1-inch pieces and save for sauce.
Place roll-ups on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes, until golden brown.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in square pan.
Then punch holes in cake with toothpick.
Mix 1/2 cup water with jello and strawberry pop. Pour this over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix 1 1/2 cups milk with instant vanilla pudding.
Add Cool Whip; spread over cake.

title: florida grill salad
directions: Top lettuce mix with a little of oranges and almonds.

title: dirt cake
directions: If you want to get fancy, use a new flowerpot and trowel to serve and gummy worms on top.

title: pineapple cheese torte
directions: Combine crust ingredients; pat into the bottom of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joe hamburgers
directions: Place in a skillet 2 tablespoons oil. Add onion. Cook until slightly brown. Add ground beef. Cook until brown; drain fat. Add tomato soup and 1/4 can of water.

title: marilyn's chicken cacciatori
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet. Brown Chicken in it. Remove chicken and keep hot. Cook onions and garlic in oil until tender. Add other ingredients except wine and blend. Cook for 5 minutes. Return chicken to skillet and simmer for 45 minutes. Add wine and cook uncovered for about 15 minutes.

title: timmy's tightwad cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients and add to dry mixture.
Add melted shortening and bread crumbs.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: one dish macaroni and beef
directions: Cook in a 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes in a microwave or until macaroni is tender, stirring once.

title: peach pie
directions: Heat ingredients until thickened.
Pour over raw, sliced peaches in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip or whipping cream. Yields 3 deep dish pies.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well. Can be used on outside barbecuing or in your oven for last minute broiling. Do not leave under broiler too long, it will burn.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice tomatoes.
Dip in cornmeal.
Fry in bacon drippings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pack in bread pan.
Place in cold place overnight.
Slice 1/2-inch thick and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ground cherry pie
directions: Combine ground cherries, ReaLemon, brown sugar and salt.
Add 1 quart water to cover.
Bring to boil; thicken with clear-jell. Turn heat down; boil for 2 minutes.
Take off stove.
Add the butter or oleo.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, then put crust on top.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put butter in iron skillet; melt.
Add sugar and stir.
Mix flour and eggs together and add milk.
Pour in skillet slowly on sugar and butter, stirring until thick.
Add vanilla and put in baked pie shell.
Spread meringue on top and bake at 300° for meringue to brown.

title: lipton onion-beef macaroni casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown meat; drain.
Stir in onion soup, flour, sauce and water.
Simmer covered for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
Makes 5 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Baste the last hour with above ingredients.

title: cherry angel food cake
directions: Mix well the Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Put in between cake layers and cherry pie filling and on top of cake. Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: st. thomian potato pudding
directions: Boil potatoes.
While potatoes are boiling, saute onion, green peppers and celery until wilted.
Add capers, Spanish olives and raisins.
Saute for a few more minutes.
Do not let it get too brown.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add a little water, if the sauce is too thick.

title: teacher's chicken
directions: Wash and skin a plump frying chicken.
Put in crock-pot; cover with Italian dressing.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
(If oven cooking is preferred, place chicken in a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for one hour, or until meat falls from bone.)

title: chicken with cashews(quick recipe, 15 to 20 minutes)
directions: Place oil in wok.
Add garlic; saute 2 to 3 minutes (don't burn).
Add chicken.
Cook until no longer pink (5 minutes). Meanwhile, microwave broccoli (4 minutes).
Cut up and mike again for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, cut up pepper and nuts to wok.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes; add in sugar, oyster sauce, clam juice, pepper, salt and Tabasco.
(These last 6 ingredients I usually have mixed in a cup and ready to go.)
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
(Try varying recipe by using shrimp instead of chicken or by adding other vegetables you may enjoy.)
Serves 4.

title: quick venison chili
directions: Brown venison and sausage in heavy iron skillet or Dutch oven. Remove meat and saute onions and garlic in grease.
Mix meat, onion, garlic, tomato sauce, chili powder, oregano, thyme, bay leaf, beer and kidney beans.
Simmer, tightly covered, for 1 hour or more, stirring occasionally.
Correct seasonings with salt and pepper.
Cook until well thickened and rich in flavor.
This is great cooked over a campfire in a heavy Dutch oven and will fill lots of hungry mouths.

title: andrew fudgies
directions: In bowl, mix first 2 ingredients together, then blend in next 8 ingredients.
Beat very well.
Pour into either 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 17-inch ungreased pan.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
(Test for center to be done at about 40 minutes.)

title: tumble weeds
directions: Mix peanuts and potato sticks (I break them in smaller pieces).
In a large bowl, melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter in microwave (do not boil).
Pour over dry ingredients. Mix and drop on cookie sheet by tablespoon (covered with wax paper).
Place in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes to set.
Store in covered container.

title: cream wafers
directions: Mix all together until smooth and chill overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and onion and boil until potatoes are almost tender. Heat chicken bouillon, milk, salt, pepper and bay leaves in soup pot over medium-high heat to almost boiling. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, green onion, green pepper, thyme, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well. Shape beef mixture into 3/4-inch meatballs.
(Allow to stand at room temperature 1/2 hour.)
Pour cooking oil into a metal fondue cooker to no more than 1/2 capacity or to depth of 2-inches.
Heat over range to 350°.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to hot oil.
Transfer cooker to fondue burner.
Spear individual meatballs with a fondue fork.
Cook in oil 1 minute or until browned.
Transfer meatballs with a dinner fork.
Dip in Tangy Cranberry Sauce.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: In top of double boiler, melt butter; add cheese and melt slowly over hot water (not boiling water), stirring occasionally. Do not allow it to get too hot.
Gradually stir in the ale or milk and seasonings.
When creamy, spoon the mixture onto the slices of buttered toast.
Brown quickly under the broiler if you like. Serve the rarebit very hot.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all together, except grated cheese and potato chips.
Put in large shallow pan.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potato chips brown.
(I sometimes also put in sliced olives.)

title: dipping sauce for fruit
directions: Chop peppers and mix with vinegar or juice and pepper.
Serve as a dip with bananas, pineapple or other fruit.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in juice.
Add cheese and cracker crumbs. Mix well and spoon into a quart casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix well with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese soften for one hour.
Add sugar and milk. Mix until all ingredients are soft; add eggs one at a time.
While mixing, add sour cream, flour and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Flour and butter pan.
Pour in batter.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Shut off oven; crack oven door until cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy zucchini
directions: Fry bacon to a crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble when cool. Slice zucchini thin and put into bacon grease.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Cover and cook on medium-high for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove lid and reduce heat to low.
Add bacon and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: deviled crab deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl thoroughly and place in a greased 1 quart casserole dish.
Cover with topping mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15-20 minutes until browned.

title: peking roast
directions: With a sharp knife, cut slits into the meat; insert slivers of onion and garlic into the slits.
Put the meat in a bowl and slowly drizzle vinegar over it.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Before cooking, pour off the vinegar and wipe the meat with a clean, dry cloth.
Place the roast in a heavy pot and brown it on all sides in the oil.
Pour the coffee over the meat; add water.
Cover and cook slowly on top of the stove for approximately 6 hours.
Additional water may be needed, so check and add only a small amount at a time.
Add salt and pepper only during the last 20 minutes.
