Serve at room temperature.

title: cherry rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix and press 1/2 inch greased 9 x 13 pan.
You will have some left over to use later.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spread tortilla chips on baking sheet. Sprinkle chicken, onions and cheese over chips. Bake about 5 minutes or until cheese starts to bubble. Serve hot. Makes 22 nachos. Calories: 20, Carbohydrate: 1g.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together and shape into two balls.
Roll in nuts. Refrigerate.
Serve with a couple of different kinds of crackers.

title: easy plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for one hour (do not open door while baking).

title: yummy lemon dessert
directions: Mix the crumbs and margarine.
Press 3/4 into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip condensed milk and lemon juice and rind until thick. Put on crust.
Add the vanilla and sugar to the whipped cream.
Put the whipped cream on top of lemon mixture, then remaining 1/4 of the crumbs on top of the whipped cream.
(Can add canned pineapple, drained, to lemon mix and decorate with maraschino cherries on top.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Bring vinegar and water to a boil and let cool.
Mix well and add to water and vinegar the sugar, egg, mayo and canned milk.
Add chopped onion, chopped celery, salt, pepper and hard-boiled eggs.

title: corn o'brien
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter until done.
Add corn and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place roast in pan.
Add pepper to roast, add sliced onion and garlic powder.
Cook for 15 minutes. Lower oven to 350° and add water and soya sauce.
Use thermometer for well done.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In a large pot or bowl, mix noodles with 1 stick melted butter, sour cream, mushrooms and grated Cheddar.
Put into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Make as any cake.
Lightly flour raisins before adding.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix at room temperature.
Refrigerate, then roll into a ball. Dip in chopped nuts, parsley or chopped chives.
Serve on your favorite bread or crackers.

title: chicken pot pie with biscuit topping
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in melted oleo.
Blend in flour, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth, evaporated milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sauce is thick.
Fold in chicken.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart lightly greased baking dish.
Make 1 cup flour into biscuits.
Roll out and spread 1/3 cup sliced green olives and 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place these on top of mixture in casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: no-fail pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Take a Reynolds Brown-in-Bag.
Coat with the 2 tablespoons flour.
Prepare the roast by sprinkling with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place roast in Brown-in-Bag.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions on top of the roast.
Add bouillon cubes, mushroom soup and 8 ounces of hot water.
Close Brown-in-Bag and cut slits in top of bag.
Place Brown-in-Bag in a shallow baking dish.
Put it in the oven as you walk out the door for Sunday School and come back after worship service and you're ready.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: white chili
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top or mild Mexican Cheez Whiz spooned in.

title: citrus jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Combine all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: In saucepan, cover raisins with water. Bring to a boil and simmer for a few minutes.
Drain.

Put cubed bread in greased, oven-safe bowl. Blend in milk and eggs. Add sugar, raisins, butter, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Allow to soak for 5 minutes. Place in an oven-safe, larger bowl of hot water.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until custard is set.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until soft.
Dip in cold water to remove skins.
Mash.
Mix yeast with honey and water. Let rise until
double.
Add
yeast
mixture to potatoes with salt.
Add flour
until
bread
dough
consistency.
Roll out 3/8-inch thick. Cut
in circles.
Place on pan to rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, using three 9-inch round pans.

title: soft drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add raisins (if using them) and drop on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top of drops with sugar and cinnamon, if you wish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry vinegar(a syrup to make a refreshing drink)
directions: Cover berries with vinegar.
Mash them a bit.
Allow to stand overnight.
Strain through a wet jelly bag.
Measure juice and add an equal amount of white sugar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Pour into sterilized bottles and seal.
When serving, add water to taste (approximately 1 ounce juice to 6 ounces water).

title: creole shrimp and rice
directions: Fry bacon in large iron skillet.
Remove from pan; drain and crumble 2 strips.
Set aside.
Crumble remaining bacon and set aside.
Discard drippings.
Saute onion, pepper and celery until tender.
Add tomatoes and juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and the 2 crumbled strips of bacon.
Cover and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Ten minutes before serving, mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and stir to dissolve. Add tomato mixture.
Stir well and add shrimp and green onions. Simmer.
Serve over hot cooked rice and sprinkle with remaining crumbled bacon.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over Doritos chips.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Wash blueberries and put sugar over them.
In a bowl, mix lemon juice, milk and Cool Whip.
Add blueberries and pecans; mix and pour into crusts.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pies.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water
then add ginger ale.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts. Refrigerate to gel.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare according to directions; bake in two layer pans.
Cool and split layers, making 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese and sugar; add peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Dream Whip; turn into crust.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.
Can garnish with chopped nuts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans. Sift together dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Blend well. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix, make out into two loaves and put in a baking dish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in just enough boiling water to make a paste (1 to 2 tablespoons).
Mix all other ingredients except sugar into the Jell-O paste.
Measure the results of mixture and add 1 cup of sugar for every 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Top with garnish (green leaves and berries).
Stores in refrigerator very well.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Crumble breads.
Heat chicken noodle soup and mash noodles. Add this to bread mixture with melted margarine and mix finely chopped onion with sage; add to mixture.
Heat chicken broth and add to mixture.
Add milk and beaten eggs to mixture.
Should be thin enough to pour.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish well and pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 400° until set, 30 to 60 minutes.

title: angie's mom's sweet potato souffle
directions: Melt margarine. Add brown sugar, flour and nuts. Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Cream shortening and both sugars.
Add egg, water and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Slowly add flour mixture, mixing until well blended.
Add oatmeal and raisins or chocolate chips, stirring until evenly distributed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Will keep one month.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10 inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peachy sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Add 1/2 cup extra margarine.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potato, sugar, butter, milk, egg, nutmeg and cinnamon in mixer bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar. Add egg mixture to cold milk; beat well. Cook in double boiler until it coats a metal spoon. When custard is cold, add vanilla. Strain to make a smooth custard.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Heat all ingredients, except chicken and spaghetti, to boiling in 10-inch skillet.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and pineapple and bring mixture to a boil. Cook slowly for 12 minutes and remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until well mixed.
Skim and pour into jars.
Seal with paraffin wax.

title: blueberry (no bake) pie
directions: Mix ingredients and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens; stir often.
When mixture is thickened, add 3 cups blueberries and pour into a baked pie shell which has been lined with 4 ounces of softened cream cheese.
Serve with fresh whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: tortellini with light basil sauce
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Meanwhile, place cream, basil, mayonnaise, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper into blender container.
Cover; process until smooth.
Blend in egg yolk.
Drain tortellini; return to pot.
Add basil sauce, ham and walnuts; toss well.
Cook over low heat for about 3 to 5 minutes, until heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: opal basil cheddar crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the cheese, butter, Tabasco sauce and mustard.
Blend in the flour and basil. When combined, stir in the cereal and blend well.
Shape into balls and place on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with the bottom of a lightly floured glass or with a fork.
Bake for 15 minutes. Serve hot.
Freezes well.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spread mixture in casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn cereal.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diana's surprise
directions: Butter an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place rice in dish.
Blend together salt, soups, milk, celery, onion and pimento.
Pour over rice.
Salt and pepper chicken to taste; place on top of rice mixture.
Bake uncovered for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes eight servings.

title: browned paprika potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for about 15 to 20 minutes; drain well.
Brush with bacon drippings or margarine. Combine corn flake crumbs, paprika and salt.
Roll potatoes in mixture until well coated.
Bake in a greased shallow baking pan at 425° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetables marinade
directions: Use any kind of canned vegetables you like.
Pour vinegar mixture over and refrigerate.

title: market bulletin diabetic apple cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chopped apples in medium bowl. Drain cherries, saving juice.
Add cherries to apples and set aside.
In small saucepan, combine cherry juice, cornstarch, 1/2 cup apple juice concentrate and 1/4 cup fructose.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add almond flavoring and pour over fruit.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Break the eggs over the apples.
Mix everything together.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, top with whipped cream or cream cheese frosting.
(I prefer the cream cheese or just plain without frosting.)

title: country captain
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and coat with flour.
Brown chicken in hot melted margarine on both sides.
Remove chicken; add green pepper, onion, garlic and curry powder to remaining margarine in pan.
Cook until onion and green peppers are tender, not brown. Return chicken pieces to pan.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: stuffed peppers or celery
directions: Drain olives thoroughly and pat dry with paper towels.
Mix olives with the cheese.
Stuff peppers or celery and slice into serving sizes.
Make sure the pepper or celery have no moisture in them before stuffing them.
An excellent hors d'oeuvre!

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape into a ball.
Best if served at room temperature.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: *Whipped topping mix is a powder found in the gelatin department.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook and drain broccoli. Combine soups and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until blended.
Combine onion mixture, soup mixture and cooked rice.

title: orange blossom cooler punch
directions: Combine frozen concentrates and water.
Place sherbet and ice cream in bottom of bowl.
Break in small pieces.
Add juice mixtures.
Stir until sherbet ice cream is partially melted. Float orange slices and cherries on top of punch.
Makes 5 quarts punch.

title: bread and butter microwave pickles
directions: Microwave 5 minutes. Stir; repeat 3 times.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat together until smooth.
Spread on slightly cooled cake.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with milk. Combine with ground chuck, salt and pepper. Shape into meat balls and place in baking dish. Pour barbecue sauce over all and bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: coconut kisses from kiss-im-mee, fl.
directions: Using electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add powdered sugar and beat more.
Fold in dates, coconut and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until they are delicately brown.

title: guffey's favorite lasagna
directions: Remove outer casing from sausage; chop meat.
In a 5-quart pan over medium heat, saute sausage, beef, onion and garlic, stirring frequently, until well browned, about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon salt, basil, fennel seed and half of parsley; mix well. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water, mashing tomatoes with wooden spoon.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer covered, stirring occasionally, until thick, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until tender and put through food chopper. Add remaining ingredients. Put all ingredients through food chopper, using meat broth. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Put in large jar the cucumbers, onion and peppers.
Combine the sugar, vinegar and spices.
Heat long enough to dissolve the sugar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate 5 days stirring once a day.
Freeze in bags.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, corn, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk a little at a time.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, marjoram and garlic.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, first in margarine, then in bread crumbs, turning to coat.
Place chicken, skin side up, in single layer in shallow roasting pan.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until fork can be inserted in chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Slowly add sugar.
Add pumpkin, lemon juice, slowly add flour, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into cookie sheet pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 paper towels with powdered sugar. Turn cake onto towels and roll.
Cool.

title: veal shanks forestiere
directions: Place the dried porcini in warm water (about 1 cup).
Melt the butter in large frypan and stir-cook the carrots, celery, garlic and onion (7 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and scrape the cooked vegetables into an ovenproof casserole that will comfortably hold the veal shanks.
Now proceed to cook shanks. Heat olive oil in large frypan and cook shanks until crusty brown. Remove and place browned shanks on top of the cooked vegetables in the casserole.
Now over high heat, add the wine
and broth to pan in which the veal was cooked.
Bring to boil and add to casserole.
Now add all remaining ingredients plus the liquid only from porcinis, reserving mushrooms.
Place casserole in oven (middle) at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove veal.
Run the remaining sauce in blender or processor.
Add mushrooms; pour over veal. Serve with buttered noodles.

title: frosty snow
directions: Soften gelatin in water; dissolve in a small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
In a blender, combine vanilla, wine, sugar, mandarins with their canning syrup, adding more juice or water to make 1 cup liquid.
Blend 10 seconds.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Pour gelatin into a bowl, add mandarin mixture and stir well.
Fold in beaten egg white, beat 30 seconds with egg beater.
Chill until set.
Serve in sherbet dishes.
Serves 4.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Layer carrots, onions and green peppers in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour over carrot mixture and refrigerate for several hours before serving (overnight is recommended).
May be refrigerated for several days to improve flavor.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in hot water; let cool. When syrupy, add cranberries, orange, sugar and pineapple. Add a few nuts if desired. Let set.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Stir together cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add olives, nuts, olive juice and pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Mixture will be soft but hardens as it chills.
Spread on thin sliced whole wheat bread.

title: squash relish
directions: Squash, onions, carrots and bell peppers are easily prepared in an electric food processor.
Sprinkle salt on vegetables and allow to set one hour.
Cover with ice and water and set aside another hour.
Then drain well in colander.
Bring vinegar, sugar and seeds to a rapid boil.
Add vegetables and bring back to a rolling boil.
Pack in clean pint jars and seal with hot lids and rings.

title: mincemeat refrigerator cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add sifted flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Add orange peel, vanilla, mincemeat and nuts.
Shape into two rolls 1 1/2 inches.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill.
Slice thin.
Bake in oven at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 2 cups of dry mix or enough for 6 quarts of tea.
For one serving, place 1 to 2 teaspoons of mix in a cup or mug and fill with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix
by
hand
flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, egg, raisins
and sour cream.
Spray 2 (1-pound) coffee cans. Bake bread
in cans or 1 1/2-quart loaf.
Keep it moist.
Take out of cans
when cooled.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and put lid on. Will keep fresh 2 weeks.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken in salt water until tender.
Line a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with corn chips (any brand).
Cover with cubed, cooked chicken.
Sprinkle chili powder, garlic salt and cheese over chicken.
In a bowl combine broth, soups and tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scarborough chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in bread crumbs and place in 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup, broth and sherry.
Stir well and pour over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice.

title: apple souffle
directions: Mix ingredients, adding margarine last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: garden saute
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium to medium-high heat.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add squash and zucchini and stir-fry 3 minutes or until veggies are crisp-tender.
Do not overcook.
Add tomato, basil and lemon pepper; heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve. Yield:
Approximately 5 cups.
Contains 64 calories and 2.8 g. fat per 1 cup serving.

title: mexican chili
directions: Brown onions and ground beef in oil.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans, green peppers, chili powder and salt to taste.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: candle salad
directions: Peel and cut bananas crosswise into halves.
Insert each piece in space in center of slices of pineapple; garnish each pineapple with tiny stars, diamonds or circles cut from green pepper and fashion handle with a tiny strip of pepper.
Arrange on lettuce and pass dressing separately.
A thin pointed strip of Brazil nut may be inserted in the tip of the "candle" and lighted just as it is about to be served.
Brazil nuts are so rich in oil that they will remain aflame for a brief time.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Melt butter, add onions and cook until tender.
Add soup, cheese, milk and broccoli.
Keep over low heat about 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Add rice.
Pour in casserole dish and cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with grilled chicken.

title: rock candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring for about 30 minutes.
Check for doneness by dropping teaspoonful into cold water until it forms a ball.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When set, sprinkle with powdered sugar and drop pan to break into pieces.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 new flowerpot (8-inch diameter).

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Place over heat; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring to hard crack stage (300°).
Add flavoring and coloring.
Cool slightly.
Lay 24 skewers or popsicle sticks, 4 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Drop syrup from tip of teaspoon over stick to form 2-inch disc.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place rice in deep casserole dish. Place chicken over rice. Saute onion in melted butter. Pour over chicken. Mix soups, water and bouillon cube and pour over chicken. Bake at 375° until chicken is done.

title: diabetic jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Boil the mixture gently for 5 minutes.
Let cool and then pour into containers and store in refrigerator.

title: sugarless pumpkin pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and spices; mix until smooth.
Pour over baked pie crust. Chill for 1 hour.
Serves 7 to 8.
May top with Lite Cool Whip.

title: belgian beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Use to coat beef well.
In 1/4 cup hot oil in Dutch oven or kettle, saute garlic and onions 8 to 10 minutes until onions are tender.
Remove; set aside.
Heat remaining oil.
Add chuck; brown well on all sides.
Return to onion and garlic pan, add beer, soy sauce, Worcestershire, steak sauce, bay leaves and thyme; mix well.
Bring mixture to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer covered 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes; simmer, covered 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add peas.
Simmer, covered 8 minutes longer.
Add more salt if needed.

title: sourdough - beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Slice off top of bread and carefully hollow out.
(Make sure there are no weak places in bread shell.)
Fill bread shell with beef mixture and put top back on.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use soft bread from interior of loaf to dip in hot mixture.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt oleo; add squash, medium onion, salt and sugar.
Cook down on low heat until tender.

title: shrimp fra diablo
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet.
Add the onion, garlic and peppers; saute for 5 minutes.
Add the tomato paste, lemon juice, vinegar, water, soy sauce, hot pepper sauce and cayenne pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in the basil.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Place chicken breasts, skin side down and thick edges toward the outside, in a 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients in medium bowl.
Turn chicken over, pour on sauce and re-cover.
Microwave on Roast (70%) for 15 to 16 minutes, or until chicken is fork tender.
Let stand, covered, for five minutes before serving.

title: hot butter rum mix
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add ice cream and spices.
Store in freezer.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonful to 1 shot of rum in mug.

title: crab casserole or dip
directions: Mix milk, butter and flour together over low heat until butter has melted and the sauce is smooth.
Remove from stove.
To this add bread (cubed with crust removed).
Add onion, lemon juice, hot sauce and mayonnaise.
Fold in crab meat.
Put in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cornstarch to a boil; cook 1 minute. Beat a little of hot mixture into egg yolks; add rest of pudding and boil 1 minute more.
Add butter, lemon and lemon rind; mix and pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix rice, mushrooms, onion
and
oregano in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Salt and
pepper both sides pork chops.
Arrange pork chops over rice mixture.	Pour
can beef consomme soup over top. Cover and bake 1
hour
or	until
chops
are done. Remove cover to brown chops last 15 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits out like fruit pies.
Put chopped apples in biscuits and fold over.
Then put in buttered casserole dish.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together baking powder, flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add alternately with water.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Grease and flour two 9-inch or two 10-inch or three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger and onions in skillet and then drain grease.
Put in Dutch oven and add tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, garlic powder and chili powder.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: icebox macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and then drain it.
Do not chill yet.
While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add onion, seasonings and cheese.
Toss well.
Gently mix in peas and remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: dick spencer's banana bread(changes for zucchini bread)
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugars, oil and vanilla. Continue beating until thick.
Stir in loosely packed bananas (or zucchini) and flour, sifted with cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured 8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Glass loaf pans are preferred.
(If you reduce heat the last 10 to 15 minutes to 325°, the loaves won't burn on top.)

title: sprouted wheatberry bread
directions: Put yeast in large bowl; add 1/4 cup sprouting liquid.
Mix in brown sugar.
Let stand until yeast starts to work.

title: shrimp-broccoli au gratin
directions: Add onions to broccoli and cook according to package directions.
Drain.
Stir in rice, 1 cup of cheese, seasonings, shrimp and soup.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix oleo, flour and 1 cup chopped nuts like pie dough.
Pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: You need one box of cake mix as well as the other ingredients needed according to box instructions for baking.
Once all ingredients are blended, pour into cake pan.
Lightly pour red and green sugar sprinkles over mixture, swirling throughout cake mixture with a spoon, then bake.
The result is that the cake will have bursts of red and green all throughout.

title: crescent ravioli
directions: In a large frypan, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce (use rest for topping), onion, flour, parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat filling along one side (long side) of each rectangle.
Fold dough over filling, pressing filling to seal.
Cut each folded rectangle into 3 squares.
Spread remaining meat filling in bottom of ungreased 12 x 8-inch (shallow) baking dish.
Place squares over meat filling.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place cheese quarter on each square; pour on remaining spaghetti sauce.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes until cheese has melted and sauce is bubbly.
(If you like it hot, add just a touch of Tabasco sauce to the meat filling.)

title: pork green chile stew
directions: Brown pork in 1 to 2 batches.
Use a large black frying pan so that meat will brown quickly.
Place meat in a 3 to 4-quart casserole and add next ingredients.
Deglaze frying pan with broth and add to the pot.
Barely cover the ingredients with broth or water.
Cover and simmer until stew is thick and meat tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add a bit of salsa jalapeno if you would like it hotter.
Delicious served with a big green salad and a pile of wheat tortillas.
Also use as a filling for enchiladas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple-raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, wheat germ, oats, baking powder, cinnamon, sugar and ginger.
In a blender, combine juice concentrate, oil, egg, raisins, dried apples and applesauce.
Blend at medium speed until raisins and apples are chopped.
Stir juice mixture into dry ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonful onto nonstick cookie sheets.
Flatten each with a fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes until top springs back at your touch.
Do not brown or crisp! Cool on cookie sheets before removing to rack.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: italian style vegetable soup
directions: Peel and coarsely chop onion to measure 2 1/2 cups.
Heat vegetable oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, carrots and celery; saute 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and liquid, breaking up tomatoes with spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover; bring to a boil, then simmer 30 minutes. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese sprinkled over top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apples;
add sugar and let set.
Mix cherry Jell-O with hot water and orange juice instead of cold water.
When Jell-O starts to set, add crushed pineapple and then cranberry mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, sour cream, flour and salt.
Place berries into shell.
Pour cream mixture over berries.
Combine bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine and crumble on top.
Bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve chilled.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with crumbs until crumbly.
Pat in oblong cake pan.
Combine sugar, eggs and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients for dip into a smooth mixture, refrigerate until serving.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator a day or two before using.
When ready to use, pour over slaw made of cabbage, green peppers and shredded carrots.
Toss.
Will keep a long time.

title: fettuccine with onions and asparagus
directions: Heat the butter, margarine and 6 tablespoons of the olive oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Toss in the diced onions to coat; cook for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden and lightly browned.
Set aside.
Combine the bread crumbs with the goat cheese (use a fork for a crumbly mixture).
The cheese should be in pea size balls; this makes it easy to sprinkle evenly over the pasta.
Set aside.
Cook the fettuccine in boiling salted water.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Line foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Invert onto serving plate and carefully remove foil. Turn right side up.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until stiff.
Roll into balls about the size of large marbles.
Roll each ball into a bowl of granulated sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on sprayed cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of floured glass.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will be very crisp and rich.

title: multi-grain bread
directions: Heat water to scald.
Add oil, salt, sugar and molasses.
Cool to lukewarm.
Proof yeast in 1/3 cup water.
Mix and stir in dark flour 2 cups at a time.
Stir in white flour until stiff and kneading consistency.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead 10 times, cover with bowl and let set for 15 minutes.
Knead until elastic.
Place in oiled bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until tripled in size.
Punch down.
Turn over and let rise until doubled.
Turn out onto board and divide into 2 large or 3 medium rounds.
Place on a large cookie sheet.
Rise until doubled.
Cut a shallow "X" in top of each loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for medium loaves or 45 minutes for large loaves.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring, then slowly add 7-Up.
Pour into large tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easter nests
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, peanut butter and oleo together.
Stir in noodles and M&M's.
Place 1/4 cup on waxed paper.
With greased fingers, shape into nests.
Place peanut M&M's in nest.

title: chocolate chip graham bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine the flour, cereal, 3/4 cup oats, baking soda, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture. Stir in 3/4 cup peanuts and 2/3 cup chocolate chips. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Coarsely chop remaining peanuts; sprinkle over the top with remaining oats and chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack. Cut into bars. Yields 2 dozen.

title: espresso cream
directions: Combine water, chocolate, cinnamon stick and sugar in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly until chocolate melts. Stir in coffee until dissolved.
Discard cinnamon stick.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Serve plain or with crushed fruit.

title: luscious fruit mousse
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Press in bottom of ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake about 15 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and the vanilla.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl, until stiff.
Fold whipped cream and marshmallows into the cream cheese mixture. Spread over crust.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Cut into squares.
Top with fruit.
Refrigerate any remaining dessert. Makes 9 servings.

title: green beans with mustard butter
directions: In large skillet melt butter; stir in mustard and pepper.
Add green beans, celery leaves and water.
Cover.
Cook 15 to 17 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender; stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fat-free smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender until smooth.
Kids love it!!

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Add sugar, catsup, pineapple juice, soy sauce and vinegar in a heavy skillet and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixture all at once, stirring constantly.
The mixture will thicken and become translucent.
If you want, you can add 1 cup pineapple chunks to sauce.
However, the sauce freezes very well, but not with the pineapple in it.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 cups.

title: raspberry and cream cakes
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, but reduce water to 1 cup. Divide into two cake pans. Divide the raspberries over the two cakes. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over each cake. Pour half of the cream over each cake. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: excellent punch
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Freeze but leave room for air.
When needed, take out and add 2 to 3 quarts of ginger ale.
Makes a slush.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix well together and chill before cutting.

title: spiced mixed nuts
directions: Combine egg white and water.
Add nuts.
Toss to coat. Combine sugar and spice. Sprinkle over the nuts and toss until coated.
Place nuts in a single layer on greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. Right away, transfer nuts to wax paper. Cool. Break up any large clusters. Store in covered container.
Yields 6 cups.

title: barbecue chicken in electric skillet
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric skillet and place chicken parts on top.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes and turn and simmer 20 minutes on other side.
Watch closely the last 10 minutes so the sauce doesn't burn.
Check for doneness.
Turn heat down, the sauce will thicken and glaze chicken.

title: quick ground meat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook meat until brown.
Drain fat.
Cook macaroni as directed and drain.
In ungreased, medium-sized casserole (2 to 3-quart) mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Can be made ahead and refrigerated up to a day.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Combine 1st four ingredients in shallow dish and mix thoroughly. Heat oil in saucepan over medium-high heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and mustard.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine and shape into a ball.
Chill.
Can be frozen.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, mix condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer pudding mixture, then wafers and bananas; repeat, ending with pudding.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma's hamburg gravy
directions: Put hot water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add onion and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add salt and hamburg; stir with a fork to break up.
Cook on low heat until done.
Put 1/2 cup cold water in bowl and add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add to hamburg; bring to a boil to thicken.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Serve over boiled potatoes or rice.

title: jewish crumb cake
directions: Batter:
Cream together butter or margarine, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Sift together flour and baking soda.
Add to batter gradually.

title: baked beans with chuck
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper with ground chuck.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into a 14 x 9-inch baking dish.
Lay strips of bacon on top of beans; cover and bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: english tea scones
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl or food processor.
Mix. Make a soft dough.
On a floured surface, knead 5 to 6 times.
Roll in 1 large round.
Butter top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cut into 8 wedges.

title: ma brady's shortbread crust
directions: Sift first 2 items together. Cut butter or margarine into mixture until it looks like cornmeal. Chill 30 minutes and then press firmly into bottom and sides of pie pan. Bake in 325° oven until lightly brown on edges.

title: nigerian beef-spinach stew
directions: Brown beef cubes in oven.
Add ginger ale, red pepper, black pepper and the chopped tomato.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Meanwhile, wash the spinach and remove tough stems.
Tear leaves into small pieces.
Slice the onions thinly and separate the slices into rings.
Slice the whole tomatoes.

title: chicken paillard
directions: Flatten each piece into a paillard as follows:
Put each piece between 2 sheets of waxed paper and pound flat to a thickness of 1/8 inch.
To freeze, stack between sheets of waxed paper and then wrap in a plastic bag.

title: grandma's can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to hard ball stage, 250°.
Put Marshmallow Creme in mixing bowl.
Stir in hot syrup.
Beat until stiff and stands in peaks.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls into plate or wax paper.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Sprinkle first 3 ingredients in greased pie pan (1 large or 2 small). Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over other and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Better if left to stand for a while.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients to form a dough. Spray foil or greased cookie sheet (10 x 15-inch).
Pour first mixture into pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar and remove onto foil and let cool.
Spread filling on this and roll like a jelly roll. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Cut and serve.

title: hot water cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and green pepper in a large bowl. Sprinkle salt over top.
Pour boiling water over and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Then drain cabbage well.
Stir sugar and vinegar until dissolved.
Add celery seed.
You can add coarsely grated carrots, if desired.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together and bake in layers in 350° oven until cakes bounce back when touched.
Cool and frost.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube with small amount of hot water.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add small amounts of bouillon to get desired texture.
Chill before serving.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening.
Beat egg with milk.
Combine with dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop 2 tablespoons size on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese baked haddock
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Place fish in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk gradually.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork, but is still moist.
Makes 2 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with fajitas or chips.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften margarine at room temperature.
Add sugar; then eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add cream cheese and then flour.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in cold oven at 275° for 1 hour and 45 minutes in tube cake pan.
If using 3 loaf pans still use cold oven at 275° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add poppy seed filling; blend.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add gradually to Solo poppy seed mixture, beating well.
Fold in slightly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan (which has bottom lined with wax paper).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow to cool about 5 minutes.
Decorate with sifted powdered sugar or drizzle a glaze of powdered sugar and milk fairly thin, over cake.

title: chicken -n- dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Bring the 3 cans of chicken broth and water that the chicken was cooked to a boil.
Combine flour, eggs, and salt together.
Stir in Tbsp. of water, until dough is mixed together.
Do not get dough consistency sticky.
Roll out on floured board and cut into square or rectangle shapes.
Cook on medium heat until done.
Add chicken and black pepper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in pecans.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 12 muffin papers in a muffin tin and freeze until firm.
Remove cups from muffin pan and store in plastic bag in freezer.
Variations of your choice can be made. Set out a few minutes (about 15) before serving.
May be used as a salad or dessert.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all dry ingredients, then add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add spinach (thawed and water squeezed out).
Mix well and add melted butter. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Stir in olive oil, Ranch salad dressing mix and thawed vegetable medley.
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg and combine with remaining ingredients except chips.
Beat well and fold in chips.

title: easy chicken chow mein
directions: Cook and debone chicken; add cornstarch to broth.
Cook vegetables	together, no more than 5 minutes, until just done, then add
chicken
and
broth sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes at a simmer.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well. Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add pecans.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken wings
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter and add 1 bottle of hot sauce.
Add vinegar, honey, Heinz 57 sauce, garlic powder, black pepper, onion flakes and second bottle of hot sauce.
Bring to a slow boil and remove from heat.
Coat chicken wings.
Place coated cooked wings on a baking tray.
heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in 2 loaf pans (greased) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cuban bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add salt and sugar.
Stir thoroughly. Add flour a little at a time.
Beat with a wooden spoon.
When dough is thoroughly mixed, shape it into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl and grease the top.
Cover with dry, clean towel; let stand in a warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured board.

title: oil and vinegar salad dressing
directions: In a 1-quart jar with a tight fitting lid, mix sugar, ground mustard, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add water, vinegar and garlic. Shake until sugar is dissolved.
Add oil; shake well. Refrigerate.
Remove garlic before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Flour and grease pans.
Makes 2 loaves of bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add the soups and the soy sauce. Prepare the rice according to box directions, then pour the ground beef mixture over the rice.
Add chow mein noodles on top.
Bake in oven (350°) for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with extra noodles and soy sauce.

title: "goop"
directions: Cook the ground beef and green pepper together until tender and meat browns. Add the garlic salt, celery salt, corn, soups and olives.
Mix the cheese through meat mixture, reserving some for top.
Bake in a 375° oven until bubbly and brown.
Freezes well. Do not bake before freezing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Soak 2 fryers in this mixture overnight or a few hours.
Grill or bake in oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in moderate oven.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Form into walnut size balls and brown in the butter in a large, heavy skillet. When they are good and brown, add the next 5 ingredients and heat.
Combine the cornstarch and water. Blend with the mixture in the skillet, tipping the pan to mix evenly. Cook until thickened.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rest and simmer. (I find more water is needed so I use some beef bouillon.)

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Pour the 1/2 cup sugar over rhubarb in an unbaked shell; set aside.
Mix sour cream, beaten eggs, salt, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and salt them to taste.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Microwave on high 12 minutes or bake in oven 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and seasonings; heat thoroughly.
Mix in 1/2 cup cheese.
Serve at once over warm rice.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a saucepan and boil for about 1 minute.
Pour boiled mixture over peanut butter, oats and vanilla in a bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Let stand 2 hours before serving.
The flavor is even better if set for 2 to 3 days.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Soak overnight.
Re-cover with water and add salt to taste. Cook in pressure cooker for 45 minutes.
One cup of boiled peanuts and 1 quart of canned, drained green beans, heated.
Serve.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Combine hominy, half of the tamales, the Vienna sausages and soup.
Gently mix; turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange remaining tamales on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top; return to oven for a few minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash and dry blueberries.
Allow frozen berries to thaw completely; dry well.
Cream butter; add eggs and sugar.
Beat for 4 minutes with electric mixer on high speed.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder at low speed.
Add flour mixture in fourths, alternating in thirds with milk.
Beat just until smooth.
Add lemon juice and fold in berries with rubber spatula.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Wrap chestnuts in 1/2 slice bacon; secure with a toothpick. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine ketchup and sugars.
Pour off some of grease.
Pour sauce over chestnuts.
Bake 20 more minutes.

title: green pepper pickle
directions: Put peppers and pickles into blender.
Blend well.
Put blended peppers and pickles into large pot.
Stir in vinegar and sugar.
Bring to boil; boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Certo; skim off foam.
Add green food coloring.
Pour into jars; let cool.
Freeze (keeps forever).
Spoon over softened cream cheese and serve with crackers.
(Also keeps in refrigerator for months.)

title: cajun jiffy jambalaya
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except green onion pieces; mix well.
Cook on top of the stove until meat is tender.
Garnish with green onion pieces.
Serve with rice and beans.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tiger butter
directions: Break white chocolate into 1-inch pieces and place in a 2-quart glass microwave dish.
Microwave on Medium for 5 minutes, or until melted.
Add peanut butter.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, or until creamy when stirred.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Brown hamburg, bacon, onion and garlic in skillet.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or simmer in crock-pot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Add green chilies and milk.
Mix well.
Cut tortillas into quarters and line baking dish.
Pour half of mixture and then a layer of tortillas. Repeat and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: fruit cake
directions: Stir and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: almond toffee
directions: Note:
You must use a heavy cast-iron skillet for this recipe. You must use butter.

title: italian meat ball stew(crock-pot)
directions: Combine beef with bread crumbs, eggs, milk, cheese, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Make into 2-inch balls.
Drop carrots in bottom of slow cooking pot.
Arrange meat balls over carrots. Combine tomato paste with water, bouillon, oregano, seasoned salt and basil.
Pour over meat; cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn to high; add Italian vegetables.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 more minutes until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and chopped onion in margarine for 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano.
Combine beaten eggs and Muenster cheese.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Pour mixture into pie shell and bake for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Stir
all
dry	ingredients together and set aside.
In saucepan, put
water, margarine, oil and cocoa.
Bring to boil and pour over dry ingredients.	Mix well.
Set aside.

title: roast beets with orange juice
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Tear off 4 sheets of aluminum foil large enough to cover each of the beets.
Place each beet on a piece of foil and turn up the sides to hold the liquid.
Pour 2 tablespoons orange juice on each beet and sprinkle with thyme.
Tightly enclose beets in the foil and set in a baking dish.
Put in oven and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Serve at once.
Great with broiled fish.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water until thick.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add a little of the cooked grits to the beaten egg, mix well.
Stir this into remaining grits.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in saucepan (or microwave dish) until cheese is melted.
Pour into baking dish (greased) and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
The top will puff up some when it is done.

title: raisin-nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Cut in shortening. Combine eggs and milk. Add to flour mixture. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Add raisins and nuts. Pour into muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done. These muffins freeze well.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut margarine into flour.
Add milk and mix.
Roll dough on floured surface and cut into rectangle shapes.
Bring 6 cups chicken broth to a boil.
Gradually add, layer at a time, of dumplings to broth.
Shake pot along, stirring breaks the dumplings.
May stir occasionally though.
After all the dumplings have been placed in the pot, add approximately 1/2 cup milk.
Turn heat down and place lid on pot.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: eileen's calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble. Saute onion and green pepper. Add beans. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.

title: savory ribs
directions: In 3-quart casserole, cook onion, green pepper and oil, covered, on High for 6 minutes. Stir once.
Add paprika, cook 1 minute.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed on mixer for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Invert on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll cake and towel together as for jelly roll. Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Unroll cake.
Spread with cheese mixture and re-roll.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: chocolate eclair or fat mama
directions: Mix milk and pudding at low speed in electric mixer until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers and then the rest of pudding mixture.
Top with layer of graham crackers.
Let down chocolate icing (from bought can or your own) with hot milk or water until it can be spread easily over top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.
Can be made ahead of serving by 1 or 2 days.
Cut in squares.

title: mom meloy's chocolate pie
directions: Melt shortening, butter and cocoa in a double boiler.

title: snow on the mountain
directions: Heat oil; cook onion and mushrooms until onion is slightly yellow.
Add sour cream, soup, parsley, wine, paprika and chicken. Heat, but do not boil.

title: orange milk freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer until it stands in peaks.
Place in a freezer container and freeze.
Makes 1 serving but can be doubled to make as much as you want.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour, sugar and pecans.
Press in bottom of greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool

title: bacon hors d'oeuvre
directions: Spread brown sugar on each 1/2 strip of bacon.
Roll bacon strip around sliced water chestnuts and pineapple chunks and put toothpick through.
Bake at 350° until crisp.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with combined bananas and milk. Pour into oblong pan (8 x 12-inch) and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Cool and cover with the following frosting:

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Cut the unpared zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook and stir all ingredients except the tomato wedges, parsley and cheese.
In a medium skillet, saute vegetables until tender crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato wedges.
Cover and cook just until tomatoes are cooked through.
Sprinkle with parsley and cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Cream sugar and margarine; add water and
sour cream.
Add flour mixture gradually; add eggs one at a time and beat well after each one.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring and beat well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture in pan and bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven!

title: ann's zabaglione
directions: In the top of a double boiler, combine wine and sugar.
Place over simmering water (upper pan should not touch water).
Add egg yolks and salt.
Using a wire whisk, beat until mixture thickens and mounds (about 8 minutes).
Beat in the vanilla.
Serve in a tall glass over the strawberries.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon. Serve with wafers, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg custard(grandmother byrd's)
directions: Separate eggs and beat.
(Don't beat egg whites too stiff.) Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Add milk slowly and fold in egg whites. Pour into an oblong pan and set in a pan of water to bake at 325° until brown.
(If browning too fast, may cover.)

title: cabbage soup
directions: Add veggies and spices to water.
Simmer until veggies are cooked.
Great for dieting.

title: ashley's tea cakes(given to me by betty kerby)
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add all
other ingredients.
When you roll out dough, so not get too thin.
Cookie will be softer if not too thin.
I bake mine 7 minutes in a 325 degree oven.
Sprinkle with sugar when removed from oven.

title: hot fudge
directions: Boil in a saucepan until thickened the milk, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Can be refrigerated and rewarmed.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using the 2 cups of milk.
Mix with nondairy whipped topping.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with layer of graham cracker crumbs.
Place 1/2 of pudding mixture on crackers.
Top with second layer of crackers.
Add remainder of pudding.
Top with a third layer of cracker crumbs.
Frost with fudge frosting.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Can be frozen.

title: cheese-caraway batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cheese, shortening, sugar, salt, caraway seed and 2 cups of flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
By hand, beat 300 vigorous strokes. Stir in remaining flour, beating until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place for about 30 minutes, or until doubled in size.
Stir down batter by beating about 25 strokes.
Spread evenly in greased loaf pan.
Cover; let rise again until doubled in size, about 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Brush top with melted butter.

title: rocky roads
directions: Melt in microwave according to directions on package.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: roasted chicken & rice
directions: Cook chicken until almost done. Add water or orange juice. Bring to boil then simmer until almost done. Add butter. You may need a little more water. Add rice and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer until done.

title: fried cabbage with noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, omitting salt. Stir-fry chopped cabbage in oleo over medium heat until cabbage is tender, but still crisp, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Add drained noodles, caraway seed and onion powder. Stir together gently.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a pan of water at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Mix last three ingredients together. Combine both and chill overnight. Approximately 1 1/2 pounds dip.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Coat with frosting of shortening, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix milk, butter and cheese.
Melt on the stove, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: catsup
directions: Put onions in blender with a little juice.
Boil all but vinegar and sugar down to half.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Yields 8 pints.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Fry sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly and done. Drain. Combine sausage, cheese and Bisquick mix.
Add water and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields approximately 6 dozen.

title: french toast with orange sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in shallow bowl; beat well.
Melt butter (2 tablespoons) in skillet; dip 4 bread slices, 1 at a time, into egg mixture, coating well.
Let drain; arrange in skillet and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Repeat procedure with remaining bread, adding butter as needed.
Serve toast with Orange Sauce.

title: diabetic gingerbread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add molasses and egg.

In separate bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves. Alternately add flour mixture and orange to margarine and brown sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix in grated orange peel.
Pour batter into oiled and floured 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 20 minutes in pan.
Use lite Cool Whip for topping.

title: makes its own crust custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients 2 to 4 seconds.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple butter in crock-pot
directions: Using 3 1/2-quart crock-pot, fill with sliced apples.
Mix in all other ingredients.
On low temperature, cook 8 to 10 hours with lid on; stir.
With lid off, cook 8 to 10 hours; stir.
Empty into pan and mash if lumpy.
Heat; can and seal.
Can be frozen after cooling.

title: confetti stuffed celery
directions: Chop up carrots and green pepper.
Mix with cottage cheese. Fill celery; cut into 2 to 3 pieces.

title: dainties
directions: Place marshmallows on top of half of the crackers.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Have peanut butter on the other crackers, ready to place on top of the marshmallows as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: dad's cookies
directions: Mix in order given, drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff - russian style(russia)
directions: Boil noodles.
Coat beef strips with 1 Tbsp. of flour and salt. Brown beef strips quickly in 1 Tbsp. butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion, and garlic, cook until onion gets tender, 3-4 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter to pan drippings, blend in 3 Tbsp. flour, add tomato paste.
Stir in beef broth. Stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add meat to skillet, stir in sour cream.
Cook slowly until heated, do not boil.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce and ginger.
Add chicken and marinate 1 hour. Drain chicken and stir-fry in hot oil.
Add vegetables and stir-fry until cooked through, about 5 minutes.
Serve with hot rice and a salad.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones.
Place all ingredients in food processor.
Mix until blended and smooth.
Spread on crackers.

title: mom's meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg, salt, pepper; shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet; remove meatballs and drain.
Combine soup, bouillon cube and water in skillet.
Add potatoes, carrots and meatballs.
Cover and cook about 1/2 hour until potatoes and carrots are cooked.

title: chocolate 'n' oat bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; 325° for glass baking dish.
In large bowl mix flour, oats, sugar and margarine.
Reserving 1/2 cup oat mixture.
Press remainder into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crust.
Top with chocolate chips and reserved oat mixture.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Ice ring orange slices or ice cream on top.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer deboned meat, Doritos and onions in ovenproof baking dish.
Mix tomatoes and soups.
Pour over layers.
Sprinkle cheese over layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered with foil.

title: wisconsin cheese soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over high heat bring to boil first 7 ingredients.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.	DO NOT DRAIN.
In a cup stir flour and 1/2 cup milk until smooth.	Pour mixture slowly into soup, stirring until thickened.
Add remaining milk and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
DO NOT BOIL.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to 300°on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Let syrup stop bubbling, then add food
coloring and
flavoring.
Mix
well.
Pour
into
a buttered small frying pan
and
swirl around until candy cools or is "tacky".
Then pour candy into a cookie sheet of confectioners sugar.
When cool
enough
to
handle, cut into pieces with buttered knife.
After candy
is cut and cooled, sift out the sugar from candy and store in airtight container.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together.
Roll out on aluminum foil with paprika.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: In
saucepan,
mix milk, mashed potatoes, sugar, butter and salt.
Heat
to
a	boiling
point,
stirring constantly. Remove from
heat; pour in bowl.
Cool to 115°.
Dissolve the yeast in small amount of lukewarm mixture.
Allow to stand for 5
minutes until foamy.
Add to potato mixture; sift together flour,
baking soda
and
baking
powder.	Add
this to first mixture;
mix well.
Place
in
a greased bowl; cover and let rise 1
hour. Then knead in 1/2 cup flour to make firm dough. Let rise
again; then make rolls.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned cream of tomato soup 4b's resturant in missoula,
directions: In sauce pan, combine the first six ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Heat cream in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Add to the tomato mixture just before serving. Yield 8 servings.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt margarine in fondue set over a moderate, direct heat. Stir in flour, garlic salt, salt, pepper, nutmeg and Tabasco. Stir in milk. Cook until sauce is smooth and slightly thick; lower heat. Add cheese, a small amount at a time and stir until cheese is melted. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and 1/3 cup milk. Cool and eat. Serve with cubes of French bread, raw vegetables or meats.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup and pepper with half the onion rings. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: crab dip
directions: Stir lemon juice through crabmeat.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or more.
Mix the cream cheese with remaining ingredients; blend well.
Gently fold in crabmeat and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil for one minute and 30 seconds.
Add oats and vanilla.
Stir and drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Let sit until firm.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in water.
When completely soaked, mash with fork and add to ground meat; mix well.
Add egg, seasoning and onions. Mix all together and shape in loaf pan or baking dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Add tomato sauce to completely cover.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 1/2 hour.
If mixture is not soft enough, add a little more water.
If too soft, add oatmeal or bread crumbs.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Put ingredients (except ribs) in pot and stir.
Add ribs and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Let pot cool and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, barbecue on grill.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until tender.
Beat the sour cream and cheese together.
Add hot potatoes; beat until almost smooth.
Add butter, chives and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Wonderful do ahead dish for company.

title: dump cake
directions: Line oblong cake pan with foil.
Spread pineapple and juice in bottom of pan.
Spread on pie filling.
Evenly spread dry cake mix on top of filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Slice butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water in a large glass dish.
Add cold water, pineapple and blueberries.
Let congeal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice
squash and cover with water.
Boil until tender. Drain. Mix
ingredients
together
and put in dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Melt
tablespoons with butter; pour over top. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: quadruple chocolate turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels and milk over low heat.
Prepare cake mix according to package.
Grease and lightly dust with cocoa a 12 x 9-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Bake 20 minutes at temperature cake mix package recommends.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips over cake.
Pour caramel sauce over chocolate chips.
Now may add pecans, if desired.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot, except corn; bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Add corn; cook 15 minutes longer.

title: pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper; place in baking dish. Top each with onion slice and lemon slice.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pour 1 tablespoon ketchup over each chop.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Place chicken strips in bowl; mix 1/4 cup soy sauce, dash of teriyaki sauce and dash of ginger; pour over chicken.
Set aside to marinate.
Dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube in 1 cup boiling water. Combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch with 1/4 cup water; stir well into bouillon mixture.
Set aside.
Pour 2 tablespoons oil in wok or heavy skillet.
Heat to 325°.
Add vegetables and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender (about 4 minutes).
Remove vegetables; set aside.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Heat to 325°.
Drain soy sauce mixture from chicken and reserve.
Add chicken to hot oil.
Stir-fry until light brown (1 to 2 minutes).
Return vegetables to wok, pour bouillon mixture and 1/3 of the soy sauce mixture over chicken and vegetables; reduce heat to 225°.
Let simmer until thick (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve over rice.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine plain flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Then add but do not beat, slightly beaten eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Stir well.
Do not use mixer.
Bake in 3 x 9-inch greased cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and ice with caramel icing.

title: dumpling soup
directions: In slow cooking pot, sprinkle beef pieces with dry onion soup mix.
Pour hot water over meat.
Stir in carrots, celery and tomato.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn control on High.
In small bowl, combine biscuit mix with parsley.
Stir in milk with fork.
Drop dumpling mixture into pot with a teaspoon.
Cover and cook on High for 30 minutes.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing mix.
Stir in green and red pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve with bread sticks, vegetable dippers, crisp breads or crackers.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: two hour rolls
directions: Proof yeast in warm water. Mix all dry ingredients and all liquid ingredients. Combine and stir with a spoon until combined. Let rise about an hour. Roll and cut. Dip in butter. Let rise. Bake at 400° until done, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich mix
directions: Grate all vegetables on "fine" side of grater. Squeeze vegetables to remove as much juice as possible.
Save some of the juice. Mix 2 tablespoons of juice with 1 envelope of gelatin in small container and dissolve over hot water.
Add gelatin to vegetables. Mix well.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.
Put mixture in glass jar with tight lid. Refrigerate overnight.
Makes about 3 dozen finger sandwiches.
